title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding mix as directed on package.
When thick, fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of an 8-inch dish with graham crackers. Spread filling on top.
Alternate crackers and filling, ending with pudding on top.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Heat the frosting until thin enough to drizzle over top of cake.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: calamondin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into 2 prepared graham cracker crusts.
Chill until firm.

title: herb barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a large shallow pan.
Pour all ingredients over chicken.

Let stand a couple of hours or overnight in refrigerator, turning chicken over occasionally. Remove chicken from marinade and grill over glowing outdoor grill, cooking meat side first, then skin side.
Baste frequently with the marinade sauce.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Spread in a greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Line with wax paper and grease again.
Top with nuts, then bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 14 minutes.
Turn onto flat towel covered with powdered sugar.
Roll up lengthwise, towel and wax paper included.
Cool.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil crushed pineapple and juice and water.
Take from stove and add cream cheese (broken into small pieces) and sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Add baby food and Jell-O.
Mix well and put into refrigerator until partly thickened.
Then add Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar, shortening, flour and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Add shredded coconut.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Slowly beat in 1/3 cup of sugar and salt.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured
cake pans. Bake until done when tested, 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: mexican fried rice
directions: Fry the rice in oil in a large skillet (cast-iron, if available) until medium brown; frequent stirring will be necessary. Cool somewhat.
Add water, chili and salt.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until rice absorbs water.
Serve hot.
May be refrigerated and reheated.

title: dang good pie
directions: Melt oleo and add all ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until center is set.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, ground cloves, etc.
(This spice mixture can be whatever you like.)
Toss biscuit pieces in mixture.
Layer with chopped nuts in Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter and 1 cup sugar over layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cookie clusters
directions: Melt chocolate with peanut butter in a microwave or in a saucepan over a low heat, stirring frequently.
Do not allow mixture to boil.
Let cool slightly, then stir in cereal and peanuts.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool at room temperature for at least 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
These will keep for up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Lightly butter baking dish.
Place 1/2 apple slices in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon, flour and butter together.
Add half of the sugar mixture over apple slices. Pour remaining sliced apples into dish.
Pour remaining sugar mixture over apples.
Bake.

title: buttermilk icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook on high for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: blueberry stack cake
directions: Add all ingredients to cake mix and blend. Bake in 6 thin layers or 3 layers and split them.
Ice with filling.
Have layers completely cool.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon this mixture around each olive, covering completely.

title: microwave popcorn
directions: Buy your favorite brand of popcorn, then open it.
First remove cellophane wrap.
Place popcorn in microwave "this side up."
Cook according to directions on box.

title: georgia peanut cookies
directions: Cream the butter with sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg, beating until fluffy.
Stir in baking soda and salt. Blend in flour.
Mix until a stiff dough forms.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.

title: california cheese and rice
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish. In hot butter in large skillet, saut onions for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly. Lay half the rice mixture in baking dish, then chili, then grated cheese, etc. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings. Great with fried fish!

title: breakfast brunch
directions: Brown sausage and drain excess fat.
Allow to cool.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread cubes and mix until bread is moistened.
Add cheese, sausage and mushrooms; stir.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
At this point casserole can be refrigerated overnight.
When ready to bake, cook in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: granny's bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in large Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.
Hollow 1 loaf of bread and spoon in dip.
Cut other loaf for extra dipping.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Bring to a boil the Karo syrup, vanilla and coconut. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Make into balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip ball in chocolate. Refrigerate.

title: scrumptious chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased casserole.
Mix together next 3 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in a heavy pan; cook slowly. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 235°.
Stir in peanuts and salt.
Cook to 300°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and soda.
Stir.
Pour onto well-greased platters.
Shake to spread mixture.
Cool and break.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Add boiling water to dry cherry jello.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Add cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: honey whole wheat rolls(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: hominy pie
directions: Brown meat in hot fat.
Add flour, tomatoes and seasoning. Brown hominy and onion in fat.
Add to meat mixture.
Bake in ungreased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Hollow out a loaf of bread; save the inside chunks for dipping.
Place mixed ingredients inside the bread.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread is crisp and dip is hot.
Serve with bread chunks, bagel chips or other crackers of your choice.

title: mrs. nolte's chilli chicken
directions: Fry over slow heat until chicken is light brown.
Drain well. Cover
(almost)
in water.	Add chili powder and simmer until tender and liquid is thickened.

title: forgotten kisses cookies
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Whip egg whites, cream of tartar, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Add chips and coloring.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put cookies in oven.
Shut off oven and leave in oven at least 6 hours.

title: carrots oregano
directions: Place quartered carrots in shallow 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with salt, butter, water and oregano.
Cover.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple marshmallow delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in pineapple in top of double boiler.
Chill thoroughly; add to whipped cream, mixing well.
Add melted margarine to crumbs.
Sprinkle 1/2 of this crumb mixture in bottom of shallow pan or dish.
Spread cream mixture over this and use rest of crumbs on top.
Chill overnight.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water until tender; drain.
In a large skillet, saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In small skillet, melt remaining butter.
Cook and stir crumbs in butter until lightly browned. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes, until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crazy salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and stir.
Chill.

title: turkey tenderloins with fresh peppers
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Add peppers, onion and seasonings.
Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes until onion is tender.
Remove from skillet.
Set aside.

title: swiss carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Combine oil and sugar in a large mixing bowl; beat thoroughly with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour mixture into egg mixture; beat thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread batter evenly into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes; turn onto cake rack to finish cooling.
Dust with sifted confectioners sugar.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix everything in the blender (or mixer at high speed) for 2 minutes.

title: almond cheesecake with raspberries
directions: Beat cream cheese, frosting, juice and peel in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.

title: copper carrots
directions: Clean carrots and cut into circles. Boil in salted water until just barely done. Drain and cool. Chop onion and pepper and put aside. Combine all other ingredients and heat until sugar is dissolved. In bowl, alternate layers of carrots, peppers and onions. Pour hot sauce over all and marinate for 24 hours in the refrigerator. Serve cold. Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks. Makes 15 servings.

title: mild picante sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes.
Add peppers, onions and rest of ingredients. Cook until done.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes about 20 to 25 pint jars.

title: chocolate refreshers(pillsbury bake-off winner)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine dates, brown sugar, water and margarine in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until dates soften.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate morsels. Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Orange Glaze.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar and water 20 minutes. Slow boil. Cool 20 minutes. Add instant coffee to boiling water; cool. Stir together vodka and vanilla.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder.
Crush whole tomatoes and place in crock-pot.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Add sugar. Add hamburger mixture to crock-pot. After cooking for 1 to 2 hours, begin tasting and season to your liking.
Tastes even better if it is cooked one day and refrigerated overnight and then reheat.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter dog cookies(really for dogs!)
directions: Mix the flour, bran flakes, oatmeal, salt and oil. Beat in the eggs, milk, peanut butter and honey. Add the milk mixture to dry mixture. Knead well.
Mixture will be heavy and hard to handle. Roll out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes (dog bone cutters are available for purchase).
Brush tops with 1 egg beaten with 1 tablespoon milk, if desired. Bake 45 minutes at 300°, then turn oven off and leave cookies in oven overnight. Cool and allow to dry thoroughly before storing.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Roll beef stew meat in flour and brown in oil.
Add onion and saute.
Add celery and water.
Cover; simmer slowly until meat is tender (about 3 hours).
Add tomato, cabbage, parsley, carrots and garlic.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add wheat, salt, pepper, oregano, peas, beans and zucchini.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into little balls (1-inch).
Bake at 425° until brown on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Shape and mold.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.

title: apple john
directions: Peel apples and slice.
Fill an 8-inch square or round pan almost to the top.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Using the box directions for biscuits, mix and pour on top.
Bake for 350 for 1 hour.
Flip over on plate while warm.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill. Serve with sliced apples.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cut garlic loaf lengthwise.
Combine cheese, onions, olives, garlic salt, mayonnaise and butter.
Top garlic loaves evenly and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Sprinkle Creole seasoning on roast.
Cut slits in roast for garlic.
Coat roast with flour and brown on both sides in 1/4 cup oil.
Take roast out of pot and make roux.
Saute onion in roux. Add about 3 quarts of water to roux.
Water may vary.
Add bouillon cubes and onion soup.
Stir and return roast to pot and cover and cook in oven at 450° for 2 to 3 hours, adding water each hour.

title: churros
directions: Bring water, lard, and salt to a boil in a saucepan. Stir in flour vigorously until it forms a ball, about 1 minute. Allow mixture to cool slightly. Beat the eggs in a bowl and slowly add to the saucepan (on medium heat) stirring until a ball forms and the dough comes off the sides of the pan. Heat a 12 inch skillet that is at least 2 inches deep, with 1/4 inch of oil, to 325 degrees. Using a piping bag, filled with a medium star tip, pipe dough into (5 to 10 inch) strips, onto parchment lined tray. Fry until amber brown. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on churros, immediately. Serve warm. Makes approximately 5 to 7 churros.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Grate cucumbers and onion over a colander so juice can drain off.
Combine with cream cheese, Miracle Whip and seasonings.
Remove crusts from bread and spread with cucumber mixture.
Put top on bread.
Place sandwiches on baking sheet with wax paper between each layer.
Place wax paper on top and cover with a damp cloth.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Add jalapeno cheese roll, Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix with rice and broccoli in large casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: spinach salad(with sweet and sour honey dressing)
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer on the stove for 5 minutes, or until sugar is completely dissolved.

title: lime punch
directions: Pour juice into large container.
Add ice cream and sherbet about 1 1/2 hours before serving.
After ice cream and sherbet are melted, add ginger ale and stir.
Serves 100.

title: "easy cake"
directions: Stir in mix lightly with spoon the cake mix, oil, eggs and water.
Add can of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine salad oil, sugar and eggs until well creamed.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add these dry ingredients together with apples and nuts.
Pour batter into pan and then spread butterscotch chips over batter.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Cream until fluffy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue corned beef
directions: Dice celery and onions.
Saute.
Add other ingredients and cook 2 to 3 hours (slow).

title: finger paint
directions: Combine cornstarch and 3/4 cup cold water in saucepan.
Add gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add hot water to starch mixture; bring to a boil.
Boil until mixture becomes clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in softened gelatin.
Add soak flakes and mix until mixture thickens and soap flakes dissolve.
Divide into containers and add color as desired.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: pear cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Beat well with electric mixer or blender until thick.
Makes 1 quart.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix granulated sugar, oil, chocolate and vanilla.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: sauerkraut with brown sugar
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine until just opaque.
Remove from skillet.
Add more butter and lightly brown sauerkraut. Reduce heat, add onions, salt, pepper and brown sugar over top of kraut.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Wieners or precooked spareribs can be added, if desired, for a one dish meal.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple, juice and soda.
Add cake mix and remaining ingredients; blend well for 4 minutes.
Pour into a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand for 15 minutes, then stir well again.
Continue every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: boneless baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt to your desire.
Spread cream of chicken soup on and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Excellent low-fat dish.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: Chop chicken breasts into bite size pieces.
Place in oblong pan.
Tear tortillas into small pieces and layer on top of chicken. Sprinkle with onion and green chiles.
Mix together in large bowl, soups, chile, chicken broth and salsa.
Pour over chicken and tortillas.
Sprinkle with black olives, then top with cheeses. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: yummy yummies
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, stick of butter and cup of flour. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread with coconut topping.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add egg yolks, two at a time.
Blend
baking
soda	with sour cream.
Add sour cream and flour alternately to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat for 3 minutes.

title: 60 minute pan dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 3 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk, water and margarine until warm (120° to 130°).
Mix into dry ingredients.
Add egg and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth, about 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest for 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half. Roll each half to fit two greased 8 or 9-inch square pans.
Place in pans.
With sharp knife, cut dough in each pan into 16 rolls; cover.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 20 minutes. Dust tops with 1 tablespoon flour.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 32.

title: prissy nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts, in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add nuts; stir until coated.
Spread on waxed paper; separate to cool.

title: southern chicken
directions: Lay chicken flat in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Layer cheese over chicken, then pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add dressing mix to cover, then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ground beef and green bean casserole
directions: Brown ground sirloin and onion.
Drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add green beans (if using frozen kind, precook), water chestnuts, water and bouillon cubes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of water until tender. Add mushroom soup, egg (well beaten), cheese, butter, salt, sugar and pimiento.
Blend.
Pour in greased 2-quart baking dish and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy red punch
directions: Heat 1 cup juice with sugar and candy.
Combine with remaining juice and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale.
Serves 20.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten out crescent rolls together on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (or follow directions on can).
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed and spread on crust.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cut in squares.
Keep in fridge until serving time.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish mix rice, soup and water.
Add pork chops.
Cover tightly and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until chops are browned.

title: cabbage rolls or stuffed peppers
directions: Cook until browned.
Add part of large can of Town House tomato sauce (Mexican style) to meat.
Roll up cabbage leaves with mixture.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour remaining sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and let stand a while before cooking.
Drop by a teaspoon into hot oil.

title: cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, not stiff.
Add cream of tartar and continue beating until very stiff.
Add sugar.
Fold in crackers, which have been crumbled into the size of peanuts.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: mary's cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, butter and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Refrigerate about three hours.
Roll.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 7 or 8 minutes.

title: mexican chalupa
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Do not boil.
Layer in casserole dish or crock-pot beginning with tortillas and ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or crock-pot on low for 5 hours.

title: savory ham bread
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of oil approximately 2 minutes. Combine Bisquick and ham.
Mix remaining oil, eggs, milk, mustard, onions and 1/2 the cheese.
Add to ham mixture and stir until well mixed.
Spread in greased round 10-inch casserole 1 to 1 1/2-inches deep.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese and sesame seed (if desired).
Pour butter or margarine over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in wedges and serve hot with butter.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream.
Bring to a boil and reach 225°.
Add vanilla. Stir in pecans. Spread on wax paper and cool.

title: broccoli stuffed baby portabella mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove mushroom stems and chop 1/2 c. mushroom stems.
Discard extra.
In a 10 inch skillet melt butter, saute onion and broccoli for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add mushrooms stems, cook an additional 2 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool slightly.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese. Spoon vegetable mixture into mushrooms caps.
Place on ungreased baking pan; garnish with bell pepper pieces.
Bake for 15 minutes. This dish takes 45 minutes to prepare:
30 minutes prep and 15 minutes cooking.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Now, beat eggs, sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and lemon juice.
Pour over the baked crust.
Re-bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut and lift while warm.

title: curried peaches
directions: Drain fruit.
Melt butter; add brown sugar and curry, stirring to blend.
Pour over fruit.
Bake slowly at 325° for 40 minutes. Let flavor marry for 24 hours before serving.

title: old el paso beef and tostada
directions: Prepare ground beef according to directions on seasoning mix package.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tostada shells on baking sheet.
Warm in oven for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Rub ham all over with seasoning; place in brown grocery bag. Turn edges down several times and staple shut.
Place in a roasting pan.
Bake 3 hours at 350°.
Ham may be glazed in a warm oven after removing from bag.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: french meat pie
directions: Mix together pork, onion, salt, pepper and celery.
Cover with water and cook, covered, for 1 hour on low heat.
Then add spices and crushed crackers, stir and let cool.

title: "crock-pot" spinach casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour.
Then cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: dirt cake(make in 8-inch diameter flower pot)
directions: Cream margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Add pudding, then milk; when it begins to thicken, add Cool Whip. Line bottom of flower pot with waxed paper.
Layer cookie crumbs, then creamed mixture; continue layering, ending with crumbs. Stick artificial plants or flowers in the "dirt" and serve.

title: squash puppies
directions: Stew squash until tender.
Drain and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and roll or spoon into 1-inch balls.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: quick and easy taco dip(hot)
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in 2 small microwavable pie plates.
Microwave until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar and lemon juice together.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Slice bananas in circle on top of first layer.
Spread drained pineapple next.
Spread coconut over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip next.
Spread nuts next.
Add maraschino cherries on top.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: confetti rice
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper towels; drain all but 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Cook rice, carrots, celery and peas in drippings until heated through, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in bacon.
Serve with soy sauce if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tangy liver pate
directions: Mash liverwurst in a bowl.
Blend in mayonnaise, onion and hot sauce (more or less to taste).
Cover and chill; serve with crackers of choice.

title: dolma
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients with the 1/4 cup water and stuff the squash, bell peppers and tomatoes.
Arrange in pan and add water to top of Dolmas.
Add salt and juice of one lemon. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook 45 minutes to one hour.

title: cranberry-almond cereal mix
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
In a small saucepan, bring 1 1/3 cups water to a boil.
Stir mix; add 2/3 cup of cereal mixture to boiling water.
Reduce heat and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: honey barbecued chicken
directions: In bowl, stir together vinegar, corn oil, flavor enhancer, garlic salt, cayenne pepper, paprika and hot pepper sauce.
Place chicken on grill, skin side up.
Cook, turning and basting with sauce mixture about 1 hour.
Spread barbecue sauce and honey over chicken.
Turn and baste all sides.
Cook 5 minutes after adding honey.
Serve hot or cold.

title: bulgur pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until softened.
Add bulgur and cook 1 minute.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Cook, covered, over low heat 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork.
Add pecans and parsley.

title: mabry mill buckwheat cakes
directions: Blend buckwheat and white flour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, add to flour mixture, add 1/2 cup oil and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Refrigerate mixture overnight.
In the morning, stir in pinch of soda to lighten the yeast.
Fry desired size pancakes on hot griddle until brown on both sides, serve with maple syrup.

title: margaritas by the gallon
directions: Combine thawed concentrates, juice and liquor in 1-gallon container.
Add enough water to fill container to the 1-gallon mark.
Stir well and chill several hours or overnight.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and 1 tablespoon water.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 2 layers. Place one in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding mix as directed.
Use 1/2 on first cake layer.
Slice bananas over top of pudding.
Pour one can of pineapple, juice and all over bananas. Pour 1/2 of strawberries over pineapple.
Top with one carton of Cool Whip.
Begin with other cake layer and repeat layering, ending with Cool Whip.
The Cool Whip on top is more showy if you place it in small snowball size, then the red strawberries can be seen.

title: mexican party dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in ovenproof dish.
Pour picante sauce on top and sprinkle cheese over.
Melt cheese in oven and serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in cocoa.
Alternately add sugar and milk, beating to spreading consistency.
Stir in vanilla.
Will fill and frost a 2 layer cake or will generously frost a 13 x 9 cake.

title: chocolate chip banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; beat well. Add bananas; mix. Add flour, soda, salt, nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole(yields 8 servings)
directions: Set aside a little cheese to sprinkle over the casserole. Melt margarine in a casserole dish to coat it.
Pour remaining butter in the above mixture.
Then pour mixture into casserole dish and sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: candy mints
directions: Mash cheese; add flavoring and coloring and mix well.
Add powdered sugar gradually.
Finally, knead with hands until like dough.
Pinch off small amount of mixture.
Dip in granulated sugar.
Press sugar side into mold.
Unmold at once onto waxed paper. Mixture not being used may need to be covered with Saran Wrap to prevent drying out.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Mix cheese, shortening and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients; blending well.
Place on greased cookie sheets in drops about the size of small walnut.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and ground meat in skillet.
Drain fat. Mix together with other ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in a covered casserole dish for 2 hours at 325°.

title: low-fat orange-scented cranberry bread
directions: In mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add prune puree.
Beat at low speed to incorporate.
Add orange peel and juice.
Mix on low speed just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and eggs in double boiler; cook until thick.
Add butter and cool.
Add the whipping cream to custard, then add marshmallows and fruit.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits completely through meat.
Insert garlic or onion or both.
Pour the vinegar over meat; leave in refrigerator 24 to 48 hours.
Place in big heavy pot (iron).
Brown in oil until nearly burned on all sides.
Pour 2 cups coffee over meat.
Add water; cover and simmer on top of stove 4 to 6 hours.
Season with salt and pepper before serving time (about 20 minutes).
Make gravy with broth.
Water may be added as needed while simmering.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, shortening, egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients; beat together.
Blend in the fresh blueberries.
Pour into long shallow pan; top with the topping.

title: baked broccoli and cheese
directions: Day before:
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix eggs, soup, mayonnaise, onion and 3/4 of cheese.
Add broccoli and mix well. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover top lightly with breadcrumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Dot with 3 or 4 pieces of butter.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: esther's cracklin bread
directions: Mix
together all ingredients.
Make into small patties and place in large greased skillet.
Put lots of grease on top of bread.
Cook
in hot oven at 450° about 20 minutes or until brown on top and bottom.

title: stuffed thighs
directions: Skin, debone and flatten thighs to an even thickness.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
It's important that the spinach be well drained.
Spread thighs with mixture, discarding any extra.
Roll thighs up, securing with toothpick or kitchen twine.
Spray baking pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° until done, about 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: black walnut sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Separate egg whites.
Beat whites with 1 cup sugar, until stiff.
Set aside.
In large bowl mix butter and remaining sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; mix until blended.
Add soda to sour cream and add to sugar mixture, alternating with sifted flour.
Fold in vanilla, walnuts and beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off.
Leave cake 1 minute more.
Take out. Leave upright 15 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt and bring to a boil the margarine, Crisco, water and cocoa; set aside.
Sift flour and sugar together; set aside.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Let set five minutes.
Combine buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream parlor banana split cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 round 9 1/2 in. baking pans. Beat butter, shortening and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat in vanilla. Mix flour, baking soda and salt. Beat flour mixture and buttermilk alternately into sugar mixture. Continue beating on medium speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly. Divide batter among 3 bowls (about 2 1/2 cups each). Stir 2 Tbsp. of the strawberry topping and the red food color into batter in one bowl. Stir 2 Tbsp. of the pineapple topping and the yellow food color into batter in second bowl. Mix cocoa with hot water; stir into batter in third bowl. Pour batters into separate pans. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire rack. Cool completely. Prepare banana frosting. Place strawberry layer on serving plate; spread with remaining 2 Tbsp. strawberry topping. Top with layer of banana slices; spread with 3/4 cup frosting. Top with chocolate layer; spread with remaining 2 Tbsp. pineapple topping; Top with layer of banana slices; spread with 3/4 cup frosting. Top with pineapple layer. Frost sides and top of cake with remaining frosting. Drizzle with chocolate ice-cream topping if desired. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and salt.
Add sugar, flour and pumpkin and mix well. Add nutmeg and cinnamon; mix well.	Add milk and mix well, then beat on low speed or with rotary hand mixer (which Mrs. Brown always used!) until smooth.
Pour into UNBAKED pie crust.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels. To coat chicken evenly, shake 2 or 3 pieces in a plastic bag containing the flour, salt and pepper.
Fill a large heavy skillet 1/2-inch deep with olive oil.
Place over medium heat.
Combine eggs, milk and parsley. Dip each chicken piece in the egg mixture and roll in the cheese.
Starting with the meaty pieces, place the chicken, skin side down, in the hot oil. Turn pieces as necessary to brown evenly on all sides.
When chicken is browned, reduce heat.
Pour in water and cover pan tightly. Cook chicken slowly 25 to 40 minutes or until all pieces are tender.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt butter
in a round cake pan or a casserole dish.
Mix together the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this mixture into pan with melted butter.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: petit pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, let set in refrigerator for one hour. Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Cook and mash squash, set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter, add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk, syrup, salt and spices.
Stir until thick and smooth. Remove from heat, add yolks one at a time, beating well after each one. Mix in squash and sugar.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks. Stir 1/2 c into squash mixture to lighten it.
Fold in remaining egg whites gently.
Pour into 1 1/2 qt souffle dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: meatball mushroom sandwiches
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beef, sausage, bread crumbs, egg and oregano; mix lightly but well.
Shape into 16 (1 1/2-inch) meatballs.

title: boar spareribs with sauerkraut
directions: Cover bottom of a roasting pan with sauerkraut.
Place over it bacon, apples and the boar ribs.
Sprinkle with caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Place tortillas in casserole; put first 3 ingredients on top of tortillas.
Mix chili powder with sour cream and spread on top, then sprinkle over with grated cheese.
Make the day before and refrigerate.
Next day bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Mix with butter and milk.
Put into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pork chop, onion, rice casserole
directions: Brown chops; do not
cook
done.
Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking
dish.
Reserve
tablespoon
of onion soup mix and spread
rest over rice.
Drain mushrooms (reserve liquid). Distribute mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserved liquid to total
cups and pour over rice. Place pork chops on top
and
sprinkle with reserved soup mix. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Sift together powdered sugar with cocoa. Melt butter. Pour butter over sugar/cocoa mixture. Use an electric mixer and add milk by the tablespoon to get the icing of consistency you want. If it's too thin, add a bit more powdered sugar. If it's too thick, add another tablespoon of milk.

title: grits with shrimp & roasted red bell peppers
directions: Butter 11 by 7 inch glass baking dish.	Char peppers over gas flame or in broiler until blackened on all sides.
Enclose in paper bag; let stand 10 minutes.
Peel, seed and coarsely chop peppers.
Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic, green onions, and chopped thyme.
Saute until onions wilt.
About 2 minutes.
Add grits and stir one minute.
Whisk in broth and cream.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed and grits are thick and tender, stirring occasionally, about 8 minutes.
Whisk in salt, hot pepper sauce and black pepper.
Fold in roasted bell peppers.
Spread grits in prepared dish.
(Can be made 2 hours ahead, let stand at room temperature.
Can be made the night before, placed in refrigerator.)
Preheat oven to 400°.
Press shrimp, on their sides, onto top of grits in single layer. Sprinkle with cheese,
Bake until grits are heated through. Shrimp are just opaque in center and cheese begins to brown, about 20 minutes.
Garnish with thyme sprigs.

title: chicken cordon bleu for one
directions: Mix
ham,
cheese, garlic, pepper
and	thyme.	Use
to stuff chicken breast in pocket left by boning.
Fold ends over to make roll.
Roll chicken in flour,
then
in
egg
and then coat with bread crumbs, coating well.

title: gluten(vegetarian meat)
directions: *If you don't use graham whole wheat, it will not stick together.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, bananas, etc.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: peanut butter-cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar together.
Add vanilla, baking powder and flour, then add "cooled" Crisco.
Add chocolate chips.
Mix all together.
Pour batter on a cookie sheet in 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° until set and slightly browned.

title: 4 layer lemon chill
directions: Mix; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and cook until brown (350°).
Put aside to cool.

title: lemon pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pie shell and chill.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add sauce and seasoning mix.
(Heat and mix well.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: pickled pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice, sugar, salt and spices in saucepan; bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Add pineapple and bring to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Refrigerate at least 5 days before serving.
Keeps quite a long time.

title: cottage cheese sticks
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter, using a pastry blender.
Add milk to cottage cheese and stir into flour mixture. Round up dough on floured board; roll to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut into 1/2 inch strips; cut each 3 inches long.
Place strips on a greased baking sheet, either twisted or laid flat and pricked with a fork.
Sprinkle with paprika and celery seed.
Refrigerate until serving.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to cooling racks, serve warm.
Makes 30 sticks.

title: fudge squares irresistible
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, melted chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Then add flour and nuts.
Pour in greased shallow pan and bake in moderate oven about 25 minutes. Cut in squares while warm.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line the outside of a 2-quart souffle dish with a double thickness of foil, extending 2 inches about dish.
Secure with a piece of string.
In a large pot over high heat, combine squash and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until squash is tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and let stand until cool enough to handle.
Remove skins from squash and discard.
In food processor or blender, puree squash until smooth; set aside.
Over low heat, melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and allspice.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened, 6 to 8 minutes, stirring.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: nordstrom's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Make golf-ball sized cookies, 2-inches apart and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all except cheese and meat in blender.
Blend and pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese and ham over this. Press gently below surface with back of spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Pie forms own crust.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Place chicken in a large, flat baking pan and cover with mixture.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
The flavor of this dish is enhanced if served the second day. It also freezes well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: mrs. sagucio's t.g.i.f. chicken dinner
directions: Call Kay's Lunch Center at 4:45 p.m. to order a 60-piece box of Korean chicken, 2 pounds of macaroni/potato salad and 1/2 pound of kimchee.
Pick up order at 5:00 p.m.
Go home and enjoy.
(Rice should have been cooked by the first person home.)

title: waldorf salad
directions: Slice banana, then half the slices.
Chop apple into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cut each grape in half.
Chop celery into 1/4-inch pieces.
Dice nuts.

title: bermuda sunset
directions: Mix well in blender.
Serve in 12 ounce Collins glasses or mugs.
Serves 2.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: In a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish, place chicken breasts; top each piece with a piece of Swiss cheese.
Mix chicken soup and milk together; pour over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle herb stuffing mix over the milk; dot with melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine vinegar, 1 tablespoon oil, 1/2 teaspoon each salt and
sugar, the oregano and pepper in bowl. Coat large cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Brush both sides of eggplant with vinegar mixture and arrange in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes per side or until fork-tender. Combine onions, garlic, 1 teaspoon oil and 2 tablespoons wine in large nonstick skillet; cook, stirring, over medium-high heat for 45 to 50 minutes.
Preparation time:
50 minutes.

title: mexi-chili casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; rinse and drain kidney beans and combine in mixing bowl with enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, onion, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese (reserve 1/2 cup), corn chips and ground beef. Stir to blend.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Spread top with sour cream, 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and a handful of chips for looks.
Bake for 3 to 4 minutes longer until cheese melts.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and heat with marshmallows.
Add jello and 2 cups hot water.
Cook until marshmallows melt.
Cool. After mixture cools, add cottage cheese and pineapple then fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill.

title: sausage and grits casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon meringue cake
directions: Bake cake in
jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) according to package directions.
Cool.
Prepare lemon pudding according to
package
directions.	Stir in lemon peel.
Cool. Prepare
frosting mix according to package directions.
Spread lemon pudding
evenly
over
cake.	Spread frosting over lemon pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir ground
beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain if necessary.
Stir in taco sauce, beans and 1 cup of cheese.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Pour
into dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top in the form of
a ring.
Serve with chips.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups of dip.

title: pinto fiesta cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Cream the sugar and margarine. Add beaten
egg
whites.
Add mashed beans and mix well.
Sift all dry
ingredients including spices together.
Add to sugar mixture. Add
apples,
raisins,
chopped walnuts and vanilla. Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Contains	3
grams
fiber and 3 grams fat per serving.

title: chilled raspberry soup
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Stir in hot water and dissolve over low heat.
Push raspberries through a strainer to remove seeds, then puree.
Combine all ingredients and place in a glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with mint and/or whole raspberries.
Makes 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1/4 bag dressing mix) and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Put rest of dressing mix on top before baking.

title: headquarters chili
directions: Cook beef, green peppers, onions and garlic in oil in cast-iron kettle until beef is lightly browned.
Add all ingredients except beans.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in undrained beans; cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Philly cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together; set aside. Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs; press crumbs into 13 x 9-inch cake pan along bottom and sides. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Let cool. Add mixture and top with pie filling. Refrigerate for 1 hour, then serve.

title: microwave nummy crunch
directions: Bring to boil until nice and frothy on High.
(I do it for 4 minutes and stir a couple of times.)

title: chicken linguine - guardian angel style
directions: Cut chicken into thin pieces; rinse and pat dry.
Saute in 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet.
Remove chicken to warm plate. Add 1 tablespoon oil, onion and garlic to skillet.
Saute for 1 minute.
Add zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar and chicken.
Cook until heated through.
Serve over linguine.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits 2 times (make an "x" on biscuits).
Shake biscuit pieces in 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 cup sugar, mixed together. Place in Bundt pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in melted butter.
Pour on top of biscuits.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry pizza pie
directions: Mix and press into pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Grind or finely mince onions, peppers and squash.
Place in a large glass mixing bowl and stir in salt.
Cover with cold water and place ice cubes on top.
Soak 2 hours (drain and rinse) with cool water 3 times during soaking.

title: california dip(for vegetables)
directions: Place picante sauce in bottom of blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: diet chicken
directions: *You may use a little oregano instead of nutmeg.

title: beef or deer pot pie
directions: If using canned meat, be sure to boil for 15 minutes prior to use.
Take a large iron skillet; oil the inside.
Place bottom crust in skillet; prick sides.
Place in oven until crust gets tanned.
Remove from oven; add beef and vegetables.
Pour brown gravy in.
Put top crust on; cut a few slits in top to vent.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until crust is brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine butter, salt and water.
Heat to a boil.
Add flour. Mix until dough mixture leaves sides of pan and does not cling to spoon.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add eggs to dough, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat until mixture is smooth. Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Cut tops off.
Fill with cream or pudding.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour and nuts together to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remainder into 8-inch square pan and bake at 305° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown.
Let cream cheese soften and mix with other ingredients.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham crackers and oleo.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, confectioners sugar and margarine and spread over bottom layer.
Add drained pineapple over 2nd layer. Add bananas and Cool Whip over pineapple.
Cover with walnuts, cherries and coconut.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: orange roughy in orange-mint-yogurt sauce
directions: Brush fish with oil and sprinkle lightly with ginger and garlic.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat source for about 5 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with fork.
Stir together yogurt, orange peel and mint leaves.
Season to taste with white pepper. To serve, spoon yogurt sauce over fish or serve separately. Serves 6.

title: green rice casserole
directions: While rice is hot, add Cheez Whiz.

Mix thoroughly. Saute onion and celery in margarine. Add broccoli, mushroom soup and water. Add cooked chicken or ham, if desired (approximately 2 cups). Combine all together and pour in greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Split open English Muffins and place on a cookie sheet so they are not touching.
In a small bowl, mix the tomato sauce and seasoning.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of sauce evenly on the muffins.
Put 2 slices pepperoni on each and top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake until cheese melts, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lime jello
directions: Blend well; pour in mold and refrigerate.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Mix with the next 3 ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; slice tomatoes and layer on top of casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cream cheese jellies
directions: Mix the ingredients together and chill dough 3 to 4 hours. Take a teaspoon of dough and roll into a little ball.
Press finger to make a small indentation and fill with raspberry or apricot jelly.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: a unique pasta dish
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Meanwhile, in skillet, boil heavy cream, salt and pepper 1 to 2 minutes to thicken.
Add fresh basil and 1 cup chopped tomatoes to pasta during the last 15 seconds.
Drain; add to cream sauce.
Toss.
Top with 1/3 cup walnuts.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Serve with your choice of condiments - diced tomatoes, shredded jack cheese, slice ripe olives, etc.

title: zucchini soup
directions: You may use more sausage and zucchini if desired.
Also less or more salt to taste.
Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven; drain off excess fat.
Add celery and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add all remaining ingredients, except green pepper. Simmer covered 20 minutes.
Add green peppers and cook covered 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: swiss chicken roll-ups
directions: Cut each cheese slice in half.
Place half on each cutlet. Starting at short end, roll up cutlet tightly.
Fasten with toothpicks or string.
On wax paper, combine the flour and seasoning.
Mix well.
Add cutlets and coat.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients in food processor or by hand.
Put in refrigerator and chill for 15 minutes.
Then roll into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Stir in kidney beans, water, French dressing and chili powder.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli with onion in broth in small saucepan until tender.
Do not drain.
Blend butter and flour in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add vegetable mixture and broth.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant about 20 minutes in boiling water.
Rinse in cold water and cube.
Simmer onion, green pepper and tomato in a little oleo or butter.
Season with salt.
Add mixture to eggplant.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook salt pork (or bacon) until browned.
Add potatoes, onions and salt and pepper.
Cover; cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
With pancake turner, turn occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.
Can be done on barbecue grill, using metal handled skillet and medium coals.

title: pizza dip
directions: Beat all ingredients up to pepper until smooth (with mixer) and spread into medium size baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of pizza sauce.
Alternate pepperoni, cheese, scallions, olives and sauce in 2 more layers.
Top with olives.
Bake in microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with garlic bagel chips.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Add oil and sugar substitute and mix well until light.
Beat eggs and add the rest of the ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rum-coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add coconut flavoring and rum. Fold in flour alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add coconut.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Let cake cool in pan and remove it before spooning on the glaze.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant in bite size pieces.
This takes a while. Marinate in lots and lots of apple cider.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and some spice to taste.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 4 weeks, or until tender.
This will serve approximately 3,799 people.
If more are expected, add the 2 rabbits.
But, do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine and shortening with sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Sift
flour,
baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with
milk.
Add
vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in a tube pan.

title: caramel streusel squares
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar and egg; cut in butter like pie crust, until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Reserve 2 cups of the mixture. Press remaining into bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ramen cabbage salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator for at least an hour before serving.
Enjoy!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup of margarine and bread crumbs.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Top with bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: vicki's chili
directions: In large skillet, cook onion, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender (not brown).
Add meat; cook until lightly browned.
Remove excess fat.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer 1/2 to 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix in large rectangular baking dish the beans, corn, onion, celery, pepper, celery soup, sour cream and grated cheese.
Mix margarine with Cheez-Its crackers that have been crushed.
Top casserole with this and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese apple
directions: Mix in ball and roll in paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp with pesto
directions: Put the above into the bowl of a food processor; turn on unit and very slowly add the olive oil through the tube until the mixture is smooth and thick. Refrigerate.

title: no bake cheesecake(diet)
directions: Beat ingredients with mixer; pour into dish or into a graham cracker crumb shell.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving. Garnish top of pie with any fruit flavored pie filling, if desired.

title: crispy sweet pickles
directions: Wash and cut into chunks dill pickles.
Add all the ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and shake jar every day. Pickles will be ready in 5 days.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange skin side down in shallow baking pan or divide between two 2-quart shallow baking dishes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes more.

title: blt bites
directions: With a small sharp knife, cut the top off each tomato. Scoop out the pulp with a small spoon, and place each tomato, cut side down, on paper towels to drain. Discard pulp. Combine all remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Spoon into tomatoes. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Measure All-Bran, raisins, shortening and molasses into mixing bowl.
Add boiling	water.	Stir
until
shortening
is melted. Add well beaten egg.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.	Add to	All-Bran
mixture.
stir
only	until combined.	Fill two greased
loaf	pans.
Bake
in
preheated moderate oven at 350° about
45 minutes.
Serve hot with cream cheese or as you like.

title: rhubarb pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, heat the rhubarb and 2/3 cup sugar.
Melt margarine in
a 5 x 10-inch pan or casserole dish. Mix batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Pour batter on top of melted margarine, then pour rhubarb over this.
Do not stir!
Bake until light brown.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add beans and sour cream. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Blend cheese, garlic powder and onions; form a ball of cheese mixture and place on plate.
Mix meat and cocktail sauce together; pour over cheese ball.
Serve with several types of crackers. When mixing crabmeat with sauce, do not make it very wet, so that it will stick to cheese.
Very good.

title: easy cheesy pie
directions: Using a medium bowl, mix cream cheese until soft; add condensed milk, mix thoroughly.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into a graham cracker pie shell.
Chill 3 hours or until firm. Top with you favorite pie filling.
Makes 1 pie.

title: dale's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast, milk, sugar, salt and shortening. Add 4 cups flour and beat by hand until it makes a medium-soft dough.
Add remainder of the flour and work into dough.
Let dough rise in a bowl, greased with oil and covered (you can use a wet cloth to cover).
Let rise until the size doubles, then roll out on a floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter, brush with oil and let rise again.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweetened dill pickles
directions: Slice pickles.
Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into jar over pickles.
If sugar settles on bottom of jar, set in pan of hot water, then swish the jar so the pickles move to stir the sugar.
Turn upside down and let set at least 3 days.
The longer they set, the better they are.

title: jimmy's gob stoppers
directions: You will need mini baking paper cups.

title: honey-and-spice glaze
directions: Remove peel from 2 lemons; trim off as much white membrane as possible.
Cut peel lengthwise into thin strips.
From lemon, squeeze 3 tablespoons juice.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine in double boiler and cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Place in fondue and use for dip.

title: oneita's yellow pound cake
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Stir in the cake mix and add the buttermilk, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese spoon bread
directions: In saucepan, mix corn meal, salt, pepper, sugar, water, fat and 1 cup milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick and boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add sliced cheese, reserving a few slices to put on top of mixture before baking. Stir until cheese melts.
Add remaining milk and beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Put reserved slices of cheese on top.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until almost set, about 50 minutes.
Serve at once from dish.
Serves 4.

title: gather round pound cake
directions: Melt together in double boiler butterscotch morsels, coffee and water.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in butterscotch mixture.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat at medium speed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Steam rice 25 minutes. Mix all ingredients and top with Cheddar in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in oven for about 30 minutes at 350°. Could add cooked chicken or beef.

title: coconut-pineapple cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 3 ingredients; add remaining ingredients, except coconut and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet.
(Allow room for cookies to spread.)
Sprinkle cookies with coconut.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned lightly.

title: bold and spicy ground steaks
directions: In a large bowl, mix meat with 1/4 teaspoon salt, the pepper and sugar until well blended.
Shape into four (1 1/4-inch) thick patties.
Sprinkle remaining salt evenly over bottom of large skillet.
Place over medium heat until skillet is hot.
Add patties; cook until browned and to desired doneness, 4 to 5 minutes per side for medium.
Remove to serving platter; keep warm.

title: sinful saladspringfield, missouri
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool.
Add strawberries, pineapples and bananas.

title: shaker pickles
directions: Layer pickles and onions in a gallon jug.
They can be packed tight.

title: forget them cookies
directions: Beat the hell out of the egg whites.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla, a little at a time.
Place on cookie sheet in little mounds (about 1 heaping teaspoon).
Heat oven to 350°. Turn off oven and put cookie sheet in oven overnight.

title: rhubarb custard pie (2)
directions: Slice rhubarb into 1 inch slices.
Mix in other ingredients and pour into unbaked shell.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake at 400° for 50-60 minutes.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in olive oil until tender and lightly browned.
Combine with remaining ingredients using half of pimentos.
Pour mixture into 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly. Garnish with remaining pimentos and parsley sprigs.
Serves 6.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Cook chicken; take off bones and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix soups and sour cream together and spoon over chicken.
Put bread crumbs from stuffing mix over chicken.
Make up seasoning for stuffing according to instructions on box.
Pour over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain peas.
Place in bowl (that can be tightly closed).
Add all other ingredients except Fritos.
Add enough chopped jalapenos for your taste.
Thinly sliced green pepper and pimento could be added.
Refrigerate 2 days before serving.
Shaking or stirring bowl will help flavors.
Use large Fritos for dipping.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Heat together the marshmallows, Hershey bars and milk on very low heat. stirring often.
Allow to cool thoroughly.
Beat the whipping cream and mix it with the chocolate/marshmallow mixture. Pour into a graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: marinade for wild game
directions: *Lemon will give more juice if put in microwave for 1 minute.

title: tangy chicken and cheese
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper; lightly flour.
Brown in heavy skillet in a little oil.
Pour salsa over chicken.
Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes.
Place cheese on top.
Cover until melted, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of tube pan.
Sift and mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until mixed.
Add other 2 eggs.
Beat until blended.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil, then add eggs, vinegar, food coloring and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix together flour, salt, baking soda and cocoa.
Add to red batter, alternating with the buttermilk.
Bake in greased oblong pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aids, sugar and water.
Add orange juice and lemonade; mix until thawed.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 25 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Form into balls and roll in cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Make 1 layer of each ingredient in a casserole dish.

title: wild rice and chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix rice, soup, soup mix and water.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Cover with foil to prevent drying out.)

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and take off bone.
Set aside.
Cook noodles in broth from chicken.
Set aside.
Steam frozen peas, onions and celery until done.

title: crab and corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In saucepan, melt butter and blend with flour. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring until white sauce thickens. Stir in the salt, pepper, lemon juice, mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce. Mix together the crab meat, eggs and corn. Add the milk sauce and turn entire mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with cheese and crumbs. Bake for 15 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Stir zucchini, onion, sour cream, celery soup and shredded carrots.
Then add margarine and Stove Top dressing.
Save out 1/2 Stove Top dressing and put on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions (chopped) in margarine.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
When tender, add cream of mushroom soup (undiluted). Crumble some crackers and add 1/2 cup of cheese and mix together in Corning Ware dish.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli
to 8 minutes.
Drain partially.
Add 1/2 stick butter and cheese.
Allow butter and cheese to melt. Pour in
greased dish. Melt the other half stick of margarine and
pour over cracker crumbs.
Put cracker crumbs and butter mixture
over broccoli.
Bake
in preheated 350° oven 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and mayonnaise in double boiler. Mix remaining ingredients. Delicious!

title: strawberries and sugar
directions: Pour sugar in a bowl.
Dip strawberries in sugar and eat.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Chop the jalapeno peppers and dice the bell pepper.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add pectin and coloring. Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal with wax.

title: swedish limpa bread
directions: Scald milk and cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add sugar 1 1/2 cup lukewarm water and milk.
Add white flour and beat well.
Let rise until double in bulk.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add cheese, butter (softened), eggs, milk and spinach.
Mix well.
Bake in lightly greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish at 350°
for 35 minutes, or until brown on top and mixture is firm.

title: chocolate cake supreme
directions: Combine and beat first 6 ingredients; add flour, powder and flavoring and beat.
Last and most important, combine boiling water and baking soda.
Mix.
Pour into batter and beat well.
Add nuts by hand.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (2 round layer pans, bake 30 to 35 minutes).
Very important:
Do not overbake.
Cake will not be as moist.

title: corn salad
directions: Warm corn with butter.
Mix all ingredients with corn; let set at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve over lettuce and tomatoes, chopped.

title: frozen rhubarb salad
directions: Combine rhubarb, water and 1/4 cup sugar in small saucepan. Cover.
Cook 3 minutes or until rhubarb is tender, stirring now and then.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine rhubarb and pineapple. Drain mixture, reserving 1/4 cup of fruit syrup.
Beat cream cheese with 1/4 cup sugar, lemon juice, dash of salt and reserved syrup. Stir in drained rhubarb, pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Stir in food coloring to make pretty pink.
Place in mold and freeze.

title: quick bread pudding
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, scald milk with margarine and sugar. In a medium bowl, beat egg substitute slightly.
Stir in milk combo.
Stir in vanilla. Add nutmeg and raisins.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cube or slice squash.
Steam lightly if you wish and set aside.
Melt margarine in a large pan and saute onion.
Add cornbread stuffing and stir to coat.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish with 1/2 of the stuffing and reserve the rest for the top.
Sprinkle "chicken" powder over squash.
Place the squash on top of the stuffing.
Mix soup and sour cream and spoon over squash.
Top with the remaining cornbread stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chiffon bars
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a greased 9 x 9 pan. These are chewy; if you like it more cakeish, add 5 minutes.

title: that pie (2)
directions: Combine condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add lemon juice and whip by hand.
(Do not use electric mixer.)
Fold fruit into mixture.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: You may use
hot
or
mild
sausage.
Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Add
tomatoes, picante sauce (may use mild, medium or hot)
and cream cheese, stirring until well blended. You may use hot
or mild sausage and picante sauce, depending on your own particular taste.
I use the mild.	Delicious with chips.

title: spinach and rice
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in olive oil and add 1 cup rice, stirring occasionally for about 20 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook on low heat until rice is almost done.
Wash and chop fresh or canned spinach and add to rice mixture.
Also to this mixture add 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Cover and cook for another 10-15 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Whip the cream; add vanilla and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing gently.
Fold vanilla cream into mixture. Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in pan or skillet with 3 tablespoons of butter until tender. Add soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add chicken that has been cut into small pieces (cubed).
Add chopped olives. Add spaghetti that has been cooked according to directions.

title: butterscotch coated pretzels
directions: Melt morsels and vegetable oil.
Dip pretzels into butterscotch mixture.
Place pretzels on waxed paper to dry.

title: easy crescent roll cheesecake
directions: In bowl, place cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix together with a fork until creamy.
Open crescent rolls and spread out on a cookie sheet to form a long rectangle.
Pinch seams together.
Spread mixture in the middle.
Fold up sides to meet in the middle and pinch together.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top when cooled.

title: orange marmalade bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Combine next 5 ingredients. Mix together.
Stir until well moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.) Grease 9 x 5 x 3 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 65 minutes.

title: potato salad with tomatoes and roast beef
directions: Core tomatoes; cut in wedges.
In large saucepan place potatoes and enough water to cover; bring to a boil.
Boil until potatoes are tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and cool slightly. In large bowl, place potatoes, roast beef, broccoli, radishes and tomatoes.
In small bowl combine yogurt, horseradish, mayonnaise, sugar and salt; pour over potato mixture.
Toss to mix.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon croquettes supreme
directions: Drain salmon. Remove skin and bones.
Flake with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients except flour and oil. Blend well.
Shape into croquettes and coat with flour. Pan-fry in hot oil, turning only once.

title: nonna romana's best amaretti
directions: Set racks in upper and lower third of oven.
Line cookie sheets with parchment paper.

title: winning stuffing meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, stuffing mix, egg, and milk; mix well. Pplace in a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan that has been coated with non stick cooking spray.
Bake for 45 minutes then pour off excess liquid.
Spread the ketchup evenly over the top and bake for 10 more minutes, or until no pink remains in meat.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Place in a greased pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Beat egg, milk and Bisquick together and pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: sauteed bananas
directions: Select bananas which are all yellow or slightly green tipped. Peel bananas and brush with lemon juice then roll bananas in sugar.
Saute in butter over low heat for 5
minutes or until golden brown.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend Miracle Whip, sugar and lemon juice and pour over other ingredients.
Mix well to completely cover.

title: old fashion coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Bake in 2 greased pans at 350° until done.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to the directions on the box.
Cook not dry, but stiff-soupy.
For consistency, add the garlic cheese. Cut the butter into small pieces for quick melting.
Break the eggs into a measuring cups; beat them with a fork, then add milk to finish filling up cup.
Add this to the grits; mix well.
Put into a buttered casserole; bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Remove from oven.
Cover top with grated sharp cheese and generous dashes of paprika.
Return to oven; bake for 10 minutes longer, but leave in the oven until ready to serve so that it will be steaming hot. Serves 6 generously.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pineapple tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill 4 hours.
Pour mixture into strainer.
Drain off juices and mound tuna mixture onto bed of lettuce.

title: mushroom deluxe
directions: Melt butter; as it begins to foam, add mushrooms and salt. Stir constantly for 3 minutes.
Add pepper, sherry and additional butter if needed.
As juice begins to come from mushrooms, remove them to a warm dish.
Add wine to deglaze pan and boil down.
Pour over mushrooms and serve.

title: california blend hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add in layers:
California veggies, rice, cream of chicken soup mixed with milk and water.
Melt margarine and pour over layers.
Add Cheez Whiz in drops.
Top with French onion rings.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Mix until crumbly.
Press firmly into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.
Combine chips and paraffin in double boiler. Melt on low heat, stirring until smooth.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate, covering bottom 2/3.
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheets.
Cool until set.
Store in refrigerator or airtight container up to 8 weeks.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs until smooth and white (not foamy).
Gradually add the sugar, salt, extract, condensed milk and whole milk. Refrigerate anywhere from 3 hours to 24 hours.
Serves 25. Sprinkle each cup with nutmeg.

title: lime sprite punch
directions: Pour Sprite into punch bowl.
Take ice cream into punch; cut slices of lime in punch bowl as garnish.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside. Brown chopped meat. Add tomato soup and mix well. Add to elbows and mix well. Layer with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy.
