title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and celery in 4 tablespoons butter. Add tomatoes and simmer for 1 hour.
Add sugar, flour, soda, salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture thickens slightly, stirring constantly.
Can add a few bread crumbs but reserve enough for top.
Pour all in baking dish, covering top with mixture of cracker crumbs and 4 tablespoons butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Make dents in ham loaf and pour glaze over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours in a shallow baking dish.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Mix pancake batter according to package instructions.
After pouring pancake batter into pan, add desired amount of chocolate chips and cook as usual.
Serve with syrup or other favorite topping.

title: grilled potatoes in foil
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings until well blended in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among six 12-inch square pieces of foil.
Seal to form a packet.
Place packets on grill over medium heat.
Grill 25 to 30 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Cook rotini.
In large skillet cook ground beef, green pepper and onions.
Cook until beef is done; drain grease and add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk, 1 cup Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and rotini.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium bowl; set aside.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Place flour in bowl; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Cut in cream cheese until mixture forms dough. Blend in vanilla.
Good used with blueberries, rhubarb or strawberries for pies.

title: apple crisp(makes 6 servings)
directions: Toss apples with lemon juice and water in shallow bowl and put into 2-quart baking dish. In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, nutmeg and salt. Mix thoroughly with blender. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Mix in walnuts. Crumble over apples to cover completely. Do not pack down. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes until top is lightly brown.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate over chicken for at least 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Bake for 1 or 1 1/4 hours, until done, at 350°.

title: s.o.s. #30
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add flour, bouillon, salt and pepper. Mix well and cook until flour is absorbed.
Reconstitute the dry milk with the warm water.
Add to beef and stir well.
Add Worcestershire.
Heat to thicken.

title: snicker wrap cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except candy bars.
Take a piece of dough the size of a walnut; wrap around the Snickers bar.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes;
do not overbake.
Remove from cookie sheet at once.
Will make around 40 cookies.

title: spaghetti florentine
directions: Combine sauce and spaghetti; toss lightly.
Combine cottage cheese and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well.

title: bacon-topped cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in large bowl; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add shredded cheeses, onion, relishes and seasonings; beat at low speed until well blended.
Cover and chill.

title: "miss leona's" hot rolls
directions: In large mixing cup or small bowl, put yeast into water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let it sit until it rises up in the container. Mix all other ingredients together except flour and let cool. When cooled and yeast has risen, add all mixtures together into large bowl.
Mix well.
Add sifted flour and mix well.
Knead dough down into small ball at least 5 or 6 times.
(Add a little flour to make kneading easier and not sticky.)

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Place layer of beans in slightly greased, flat casserole.
Add 1/2 of onions and bacon.
Repeat and pour part of vinegar, sugar and grease over beans.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered, and 30 minutes, covered.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Place rhubarb, pineapple and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar, salt and water.
Boil these ingredients for 10 minutes, then add pineapple and boil for 7 minutes.
Take off heat; add Jell-O and stir together.
Yield:
2 pints.

title: chicken - shews!
directions: You will need a wok for this recipe.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Grease and flour pizza pan.
Combine flour, salt, oregano, pepper, eggs and milk, mixing until smooth.
Pour batter into pan so it covers bottom.
Bake on low rack in oven at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add pizza sauce, cheese, pepperoni or whatever else you like.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche dish or 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground meat and onion over medium heat until brown, drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and spread all in plate.
Sprinkle with chiles.
Mix milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes. Remove from oven and top with tomatoes and grated cheese.
Return to oven and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: banana nut cake(probably the best dessert we make at starting from scratch)
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix in bananas until batter is smooth.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done, about 25 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Boil corn in water for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain.
If needed, add enough liquid for 3 cups.
Add pectin; boil.
Add sugar and boil 2 to 3 minutes until at jelly stage.
It tastes like apple jelly.
Put in jelly glasses.

title: dilled cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers. Combine water, vinegar and salt for the brine. Bring to a boil.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Add spices to each jar. Fill jar within 1-inch of top with brine.
Cook in jars in boiling water 5 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Crush coconut, pecans, cornflakes and oats to very fine. Combine all ingredients; mix real good.
Dip with teaspoon and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in water and flatten cookie.
Do not place close together as they will spread some. Bake at 320° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Makes 7 dozen or more, depending on the size of your spoon.
Let them cool on the pan and they will come loose very easily.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook the rice in chicken broth. Cool slightly. Mix all the ingredients together and pour into salad bowl. Chill and serve.

title: peanut patty candy
directions: Combine
sugar, Karo and water.
Boil 5 minutes, remove from heat and add peanuts, oleo, vanilla and a little red cake coloring.
Beat
until
mixture
is
light
pink
and has lost gloss.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges, pineapple and strawberries.
Don't use juices in the salad.
Mix together, except bananas, and then when ready to serve, add bananas.

title: delicious casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger meat with onions or onion salt.
Slice raw potatoes into casserole dish (enough for family).
Top with browned meat.
Heat together the soups; pour over potatoes and meat.
Cover; bake at least 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Usually do not need to add additional seasoning.
Very good.

title: black magic cake
directions: Mix everything together at one time, adding the hot coffee last.
The batter will be very thin.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Very good with cream cheese frosting.
Whipped cream is good too.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas lengthwise and place in pie crust.
Cover with ice cream.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.
Freeze.
Just before serving, pour hot chocolate syrup over pie.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder, and soda.
Add the chocolate chips and grated Hershey bar.
Roll into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes. Makes 112 cookies.

title: jen h agel cookies(originated in holland)
directions: Heat
oven
Lightly	grease	jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x
1-inch.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk. Add flour and cinnamon and mix well.	Pat into pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Just before done, add ketchup or BBQ sauce on top.

title: poor man cake
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins; cook slowly for 15 minutes. Add butter; cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cream cheese flan
directions: Caramelize 1 cup sugar and pour in pie pan.
Mix milk, cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth in blender. Pour over caramelized sugar.
Set pan into a larger container with one-inch of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool slightly before turning out on platter.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars. Stir in egg.
Add vanilla and water. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Add nuts and semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Mix well. Drop by half teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all together.
Spoon drop patties into skillet and fry until brown on both sides (oil or shortening may be used).

title: easy-made brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood surprise
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add bell pepper and tomatoes; blend for about 2 or 3 seconds.
Add crabmeat; blend for 2 or 3 seconds. Place all of the above in a broiler-safe (oven-to-table) container.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.*

title: hidden apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch round pan.
In a small bowl combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Dip biscuits in melted margarine, then sugar mixture. Arrange biscuits in prepared pan, overlapping 15 biscuits around outer edge, overlap remaining 5 biscuits in center.
Place an apple slice between biscuits.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
(Cover with foil if necessary to prevent excessive browning.)

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies.
Reduce heat to 220°; cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dip tortilla in oil until limp. Fill with 1/4 cup cheese and olives.
Bake 5 minutes.
Garnish with reserved cheese.

title: party punch
directions: Combine 2 quarts boiling water, sugar and citric acid in a ceramic, heatproof container, stirring until citric acid dissolves.
Combine pineapple juice, next 3 ingredients and citric acid mixture in a large plastic container.
Divide mixture evenly into 4-gallon size heavy-duty zip top plastic bags; freeze.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and spices.
Spread in pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over the top.
Sprinkle with onion, pepper and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top
with cheese and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: house of grace tea
directions: Mix sugar, tea and lemonade.
Add water and grape juice to make a gallon and refrigerate.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add flour and salt and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Chill dough.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust and chill 3 hours. Top with strawberries and glaze.

title: tangy cole slaw
directions: With a fork, gradually stir vinegar into mayonnaise, keeping smooth.
Add sugar and salt; mix well.
Pour over cabbage and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauteed chicken breasts with summer vegetables
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning once, until browned, about 10 minutes.
Pour chicken broth over chicken; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and basil to pan.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Season with additional salt and pepper to taste. Transfer chicken and vegetables to a platter and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Top with corn flakes and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: christmas mix
directions: Dump all ingredients together in large Tupperware bowl and mix well.
Leave stored in bowl.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine 2 cups crushed Oreos (food processor or blender works well) and two tablespoons margarine, melted.
Press in bottom and up sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: my sister's favorite banana bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas, shortening and milk.
Beat until well blended. Add eggs and remaining flour.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Lightly brown meat in oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Add noodles. Drop cottage or Ricotta cheese mixture evenly with a spoon over noodles. Sprinkle cheese with spaghetti sauce mix, parsley flakes, basil and salt. Add tomato juice. Cover skillet. When steam appears, turn switch to lowest heat. Cook for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top. Return cover and let stand on warm until cheese melts. Serve and enjoy.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan add sugar and cornstarch.
Stir and mix. Pour into the mixture 2 cups of milk.
Cook on medium heat until mixture bubbles.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks and reserve whites for meringue.
Add some of the hot mixture to the egg yolks.
Beat together.
Pour back into the mixture.
Return to medium heat for 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
When thick, add flavoring, margarine and coconut. Cool and pour into a baked pie shell for deep dish filling recipe. Top with meringue or Cool Whip and coconut.

title: marianna's muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugars, baking powder and soda, salt, raisins and chopped nuts.
Then whisk together eggs, sour cream, oil and vanilla.
Make a well in dry ingredients, pour in liquid mixture and stir to combine.
Spoon into paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until they are done.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Spread bean dip in an 8-inch circle on a large plate.
Mix sour cream and taco sauce together.
Spread on top of bean dip. Then layer on top of that, the onions, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.
Serve with thin style corn chips.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Fry until light brown.

title: old-fashioned split pea soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine peas, water, ham bone, onions and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove bone, cut off bits of meat and return to soup along with celery, carrots, potatoes and remaining seasonings.
Cook 45 minutes.
Serve with French bread.
Yields 12 servings.
Better the second day.

title: crabmeat english muffins
directions: Mix
together
and
spread on English muffins.	Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then broil until done.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Prepare 10 bowls and 1 chafing dish.
Crumble Fritos in one bowl.
Crumble Waverly Wafers in a bowl.
Have cooked rice for 14 in a chafing dish.
Prepare Mexican Fiesta Meat Sauce; put into a bowl.
Grate cheese; put into bowl.
Chop tomatoes and put into serving bowl.
Put the shredded lettuce into a bowl.
Put the chopped onion in a bowl.
Put the chopped ripe olives, the chopped stuffed olives and the chopped pecans into three separate bowls. Form a buffet line, 11 separate dishes.
Serve with bread and fruit.

title: praline pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in pan.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add brown sugar and cream until light and fluffy (5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each egg. Fold in flour just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup pecans.
Spoon batter into pan and place on baking sheet in oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes and remove.
Makes 16 servings.

title: new england brownie pudding
directions: Mix together brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter. Pour boiling water over top.
(This will make a sauce in bottom of pan when pudding is done.) Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 or 8.

title: beefy spanish rice
directions: I cook this in the microwave.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let margarine get room temperature. Grate cheese. Mix all ingredients, may have to add a little more flour to work with it without it sticking to hands. Put through cookie press and bake at 300° for about 12 minutes. Don't bake until brown, they will be burnt.

title: frozen pumpkin delight
directions: Coat 8-inch square baking dish with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with half gingersnap crumbs.
Stir pumpkin, sugar, 1/2 cup nuts and pumpkin spice in bowl until well blended.
Stir ice cream in large bowl until smooth.
Stir in pumpkin until well blended.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Place plastic wrap on surface.
Cover with foil and freeze at least 4 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in butter in a large skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tarragon and next four ingredients.
Bring to a boil; add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly 5 to 6 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over fettuccine.

title: golden rod eggs
directions: Scald milk.
Melt butter, add flour and seasonings.
Add hot milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until makes a thin gravy.
Peel eggs.
Mince whites finely and season.
Add egg whites to white sauce and pour over toast.
Grate egg yolks or put through a sieve.
Sprinkle over toast and white sauce mixture.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken divine
directions: Clean chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs, parsley, cheese and garlic.
Melt butter.
Roll chicken in melted butter.
Roll and cover with dry mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Place all ingredients in roaster.
Add warm water to cover.
Bake in slow oven (300°) until beans are tender and most of liquid is absorbed, 3 to 4 hours.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter or oleo in a small skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic. Cook and stir 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in artichoke hearts, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, mustard and black pepper.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Separate 1 can of dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise in half, forming 2 triangles.
Place rounded teaspoonful of filling on short end of each triangle.
Roll up, starting on the shortest end and rolling to opposite point.
Place, point side down, on ungreased baking sheet. Curve into crescent shapes.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: sausage-stuffed chicken breast
directions: Preheat oven
With a sharp knife, cut a pocket in the
thickest
part
of
each
breast half; set aside.
In a large bowl,
mix
sausage,
cup of spaghetti sauce, bread crumbs, oregano,
parsley
and
garlic
powder
until blended. Stuff 1/8 of
mixture
into each pocket.
Secure with a wooden pick.
Place in
a
shallow
quart baking dish.
In a small bowl, mix remaining spaghetti sauce and wine.
Pour half of the mixture over
chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 35 minutes. Pour remaining sauce mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Remove wooden picks.
Spoon sauce over before serving. Serves 8.

title: lot ya kair now
directions: While beef is partly frozen slice as thin as possible.
Pour soy sauce with sugar over beef.
Marinate 1 hour.
Cut bell pepper and tomatoes in cubes.
Heat oil, garlic and ginger.
After one minute, remove garlic.
Add pepper and saute 3 minutes.
Stir often.
Add beef and cook 3 minutes more.
Add tomatoes, immediately add soy sauce blended with cornstarch.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Cook for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: macaroni italian(weight watchers)
directions: Place tomato juice, bouillon cube, onion flakes and garlic in a saucepan.
Add Italian seasonings.
Simmer on low heat until thick. Fold in macaroni and cheese.
Put in ovenproof dish and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.
With rotary beater, beat together butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well each time. Stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternate, adding the dry ingredients and milk to the zucchini mixture.
Add nuts last. Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour, testing with toothpick.
Cool 15 minutes in pan; remove from pan and cool thoroughly on rack. Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: fluffy potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and vanilla until light.
Add potatoes and shortening.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to potato mixture, beating well.
Chill dough 3 hours. Fry in deep hot fat (375°) for about 3 minutes, or until brown, turning once.
Drain.
Dip in sugar.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put Cool Whip in large bowl.
Add instant pudding and whip up. Add Amaretto to flavor.
Refrigerate.
Dip assorted chunks of fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and vanilla until well blended. Carefully add sugar; mix until smooth and of desired spreading consistency.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Soften oleo and mix with powdered sugar and flour.
Put mixture in bottom of 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Pat it down to make a crust.

title: granny lona cox's liniment remedy for colds and arthritis
directions: Mix all ingredients together and rub it on whatever hurts.

title: bread bowl with spinach dip
directions: Mix dip ingredients and chill overnight.
To serve, hollow out bread loaf to make bowl.
Save bread crumbs for dipping.
Fill bread bowl with dip.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Serve immediately.

title: chimichangas(leftover meal)
directions: In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onions.
Cook until clear.
Add meat, olives, enchilada sauce and hot peppers to taste.
Divide mixture among the flour tortillas.
Fold ends in; roll into a packet (you may fasten with toothpicks, if necessary). Heat oil to hot.
Brown for 1 minute on each side.
Serve on bed of lettuce with cheese on top and tomatoes on side.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes in skins.
Peel and grate.
Put half in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine chestnuts, soup, cheese and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over broccoli and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with onion rings.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: my favorite cookies(dog biscuits)
directions: Combine flours, milk powder, oats, cornmeal and sugar.
Cut in shortening and stir in egg. Dissolve bouillon in water.
Pour into flour mixture and stir to moisten.
Knead with dough hook or on floured board by hand. Roll into log and slice 1/4-inch thick or less.
Vary size of slice to suit size of dog.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown and dry.
Cool on rack. Store airtight.

title: pineapple goulash pie
directions: Mix together Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add the pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix together well and put in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: apple torte
directions: Stir together in large bowl, apples and nuts.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sift over apples and nuts and stir well until all coated.
Beat egg.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir into apple-nut mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mushroom rice pilaf
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add rice and mix well. Stir mushrooms and soups together.
Mix with rice.
Put in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.
Stir a couple of times.
Sprinkle cheese on top and put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Melt the cream cheese.
Mix lime jello and cream cheese together.
Mix together the sugar and water; pour over jello and cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Add nuts and stir in 2 1/2 cups cold water.
Mix all together.
Put in dish; stir often.

title: barbecued hamwich
directions: Heat the first four ingredients together, then add the ham. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve in a bun.

title: crab cracker spread
directions: In a blender mince crabmeat.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers.

title: nappa salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Saute noodles, almonds and sesame seeds in one stick butter, stirring constantly until brown.
Cool.
Add to cabbage and onions.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk, stirring until smooth. Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well.

Press half of cake mix into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate pieces and 1/2 cup walnuts over crust. Drizzle with caramel mixture. Top with rest of remaining cake mixture, pressing gently onto caramel. Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool slightly. Chill and cut into bars.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in large clean jar.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over mushrooms.
Cover tightly; turn jar to make sure all mushrooms are coated.
Allow to stand at room temperature 2 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: summer tomato sauce
directions: In a large bowl, combine the tomatoes, olives, scallions, garlic, salt, pepper and basil.
Gently toss in olive oil.
Cover and let stand for at least 2 hours for flavors to develop.
To serve, toss the cooked pasta into the prepared sauce and serve at room temperature.

title: special cabbage slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion.
Mix together in large bowl.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, salt and salad oil.
Pour the boiling mixture over the cabbage and onion, but do not touch it.
Leave as is for 1 1/2 hours, then mix or toss together.
Store in covered container in refrigerator at least 12 hours before serving.
This will keep quite awhile in refrigerator.
Great with barbecue and baked beans.

title: savory chicken tarragon
directions: Melt margarine in a 4-quart saucepan; add onion and garlic and saute for 1 minute. Add chicken, carrots, parsley, tarragon and pepper; cook until chicken is lightly browned.

title: sausage and egg casserole(make night before)
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Place broken up pieces of bread on bottom of casserole dish.
Put sausage over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper and pour over it all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Delicious breakfast casserole.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and marinate 24 hours.
Serve with crackers or wafers.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted. Add cooked spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat. Serves 4 or 5.

title: glazed chicken bits
directions: Using a wire whisk, in a small mixing bowl, combine honey, ketchup, soy sauce, lemon juice, ginger root and garlic.
In an 8-inch microwave glass pie plate, arrange cubes.
Pour honey mixture over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Cook chicken mixture on High for 2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Let stand 1 minute until chicken is cooked through. Serve over rice.
Serves 2. Contains 202 calories, 1 gm fat and 307 mg sodium.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix (dry), margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumbly mixture. Press remaining crumbly mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange apple slices on mixture in pan.
Beat sour cream and egg until blended; spread over apples.
Sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until topping is light golden brown; cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chinese rice
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Chop vegetables and ham, then stir-fry in skillet or wok.
Scramble eggs and add to vegetables and stir.
Mix vegetables and eggs with rice.
Serve in bowl with soy sauce and desired amount of French onion dip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook 12 to 15 minutes, boiling. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: mary's hot sauce
directions: Boil jalapeno peppers, onion, and all tomatoes in a small pot until soft. Put in the blender, adding cilantro, garlic powder and salt. Blend the sauce to thickness desired.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs well.
Add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add jar of carrots.
Mix well.
Add flour, nuts and raisins to mixture.
Mix well.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until pick comes out clean. Serve with cream cheese or butter.

title: 5 star salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake in 375° oven until firm and lightly browned (about 45 minutes).
Unmold and serve hot, plain or with mushroom sauce or chilled and sliced for salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candied mint leaves or violets
directions: Beat egg white until frothy and add juice.
Dip or paint leaves or flowers with mixture.
Spoon sugar carefully on flowers. Place on wax paper to dry.
When dry, put in an airtight container.

title: seven layer salad
directions: This dish is simple and you can be creative with the layers. Use the size of salad bowl for the amount of servings you would like from this salad.

title: lemon nut balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add and mix in lemon peel. Stir flour and salt together and blend into butter mixture.
Mix in nuts.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
While warm, roll in 2 cups sifted confectioners sugar which has had 1 1/2 tablespoons of finely grated lemon peel added to it.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: pork chops baked with apples
directions: *I use 1 pint home canned applesauce.

title: beef-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake uncovered. Serves 4-6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach by squeezing excess water out of spinach.
Mix first 5 ingredients until creamy.
Add spinach and mix thoroughly.
Chill in the fridge for an hour.
Serve with chunks of bread, vegetables or crackers.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with slices of apple, chopped slightly, and bits of butter; roll like a jelly roll and cut in pieces about 1 1/2 inches thick; drop into boiling sauce and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Simmer on low heat for approximately 30 to 40 minutes for best flavor.
Serve on 6-inch long rolls (not hot dog buns) with Polish or any other mustard and chopped onions, if desired.

title: blondies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in 8 or 9 x 13-inch dish in 350° oven for about 20 minutes until done.
Cut while warm.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape in one-inch balls.
Chill overnight.
Mix paraffin and chocolate chips.
Melt in a double boiler.
Drop Bonbons and remove quickly.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put in ribs with sauce and cook; salt to taste.
Oregano may be added.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain well. In a large pot, put hamburger, juice and veggies.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.
Serves 3 or 4.
Good with slices of toasted French bread.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter candy bars
directions: Beat together honey and dry milk until smooth.
Blend in peanut butter.
Pat into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and drizzle over candy.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: raisin (easter) bread(6 loaves)
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: molasses sour cream cutouts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add molasses and then sour cream in which baking soda has been dissolved. Combine flour and spices; add to mixture.
Place in refrigerator 1 hour.
Roll and cut 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Combine.
Can also be used for potato salad dressing.

title: crescent vegetable pizza squares
directions: On a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet, press and spread crescent rolls together to form crust.

Mix the cream cheese and dressing together. Slightly bake crust at 375° until very slightly browned (about 5 to 7 minutes). Cool. Spread the cream cheese mixture over cooled crust just before serving.
Top with raw vegetables. Cut and serve.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Add the yeast cake to the cooled milk.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift in the flour and salt.
Add yeast-milk mixture.
Stir in the beaten eggs.
Let rise about 2 hours.
Knead smooth in bowl.
Grease top.
Cover; set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out very thin, into 12-inch circles.
Spread with butter.
Cut in wedges.
Roll up toward point.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: easy puffed oven pancake(german pancake)
directions: Place margarine or butter in a 10 to 12-inch ovenproof skillet. Place in 400° oven for 3 to 5 minutes or until margarine or butter melts.
In a bowl, beat eggs with beater. Add flour, milk and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Immediately pour into hot skillet. Bake about 25 minutes or until puffed and well browned. Serve hot with lemon wedges to squeeze and powdered sugar to sprinkle over pancakes.
Also nice with fresh berries or jam. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheesy grits
directions: Heat milk, water, salt and pepper to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually add grits.
Reduce heat.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese and onions. Stir 1 cup of hot mixture in eggs.
Stir into remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cherry macaroons
directions: Mix almond extract into condensed milk.
Then combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet, which is covered with parchment paper.
A heavily greased cookie sheet can be used, but cookies still tend to stick.

title: ethel's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with desired cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: caramel filling
directions: Melt sugars and butter on low heat.
Add milk.
Put on stove; let boil about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool, then add powdered sugar.

title: italian spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and pepper on low heat.
Drain meat. Add tomato sauce, paste, sauce mix, water, sugar, oregano and garlic.
Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In baking dish, mix together the soups and water.
Sprinkle rice over mixture.
Place chicken on top.
Cover tightly with foil (do not open) and bake in oven for 2 hours at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: Blend Scramblers, sugar, cinnamon and milk in a shallow dish. Heat margarine in skillet until bubbly, but not browned.
Dip bread in Scramblers mixture, coating both sides thoroughly.
Fry until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
Serve hot with syrup and a sprinkle of confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 servings.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Heat 2 cups water to boiling; dissolve Jell-O in it.
Add remaining water.
Pull apart corned beef.
Chop onion, eggs, pepper and celery, fine.
Add to Jell-O.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, or mold.
Chill.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce; stir 1/2 cup into ground beef along with chilies, 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese and 1/2 can fried onions.
Mix well. Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stuff cooked shells with ground beef mixture.
Arrange shells in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Monterey Jack cheese and fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until thick and lemon-colored.
Melt the chocolate with the water in a baking dish in a 350° oven for a few minutes.
Do not stir until chocolate is creamy.
Add egg yolks and sugar while chocolate is still warm.
Beat egg whites with pinch of salt until stiff.
Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites until there are no streaks.
Whip cream and add vanilla. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Spoon into serving bowl or individual cups.
Chill for 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates in quarters; pour hot water, butter, sugar and salt. Cool.
Sift flour and soda and add.
Add eggs and nuts.
Beat all together.
Put into bread dish (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Make into sandwiches with cream cheese, a real treat.

title: graham cracker fruit pie(this is an easy pie to make.)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs well.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Add 1 can pie fruit, and serve.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender. Drain and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients (except Mozzarella cheese).
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Spread with 1/2 cottage cheese filling. Add 1/2 meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice; mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Chill.
Remove side of pan.
Spread sour cream on cheesecake.
Serve with cherry topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together strawberries and glaze.
Mix sugar, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Break cake into big pieces.
Put pieces into mixture.
Put 1/2 of it in serving dish.
Top with 1/2 strawberry glaze mix.
Put last 1/2 of cake into serving dish.
Top with glaze mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, soup and sour cream.
Combine stuffing and melted butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 on bottom of dish.
Spoon squash mixture over, then spoon remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix with spoon.
Pour into greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch). Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: kosher dills
directions: Soak in cold water
for
5 hours enough cucumbers for 7 quarts, then slice and put
in
jars.
In
bottom of each jar, put 1/4 teaspoon alum,
clove garlic or 1/2 teaspoon minced garlic and scant 1 teaspoon dill.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over pickles and seal.

title: deyon's special ribs
directions: Bake in a 350° oven.
Bake for 2 hours or until tender in a covered pan.

title: idaho potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; add alternately with milk, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased pan, 13 x9 x 2-inch.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Chill thoroughly.
Spread sour cream on top.

title: chili dog casserole
directions: Pour 1 can of chili in the bottom of a baking pan.
Roll hot dogs in tortillas; put seam side down in chili.
Top with layer of cheese.
Put another can of chili on top of hot dogs and cheese. Put final layer of cheese on.
Place in oven at 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix above.
Heat in microwave 6-8 minutes.
Top with cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm with Ritz crackers or chips.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients as you would for pie dough and roll 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar, apples and cinnamon. Roll up and cut like cinnamon rolls.
Put in baking pan.

title: flavored veal chops
directions: Rub garlic over both sides of chops.
Heat olive oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
Add veal chops.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes over medium heat, turning once.
Transfer to plate.
Sprinkle with salt. Keep warm.
Drain excess fat from skillet.
Cook and stir over high heat 1 minute or until desired.
Stir in sesame oil.
Pour sauce over chops.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 2.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut eggplant into slices (not too thick).
Dip each slice, first in egg, then into crumbs.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Drain fruit, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups liquid.
Combine pudding and liquid in pan.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and fruit.
Chill for several hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Combine meat and onions in skillet and cook until no pink shows, add salt and pepper to taste.
At same time cook spaghetti as per instructions on box.
Empty tomatoes (crushed), tomato sauce and beans in 8 qt. nonstick pot and stir, add spaghetti with water and stir.
Drain meat and onions and add to pot and stir. Bring to boil and lower heat to simmer slowly.
Stir occasionally to distribute heat.
Do not overstir.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift cake mix, flour and jello together into large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add oil, mixing well.
Mix in strawberries and
juice.
Pour into pans and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in heavy frying pan.
Sprinkle on dry ingredients and let cook slowly for about 30 seconds. Gradually add milk and bring to a slow boil.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Serve over canned biscuits.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on rolls.
(Rolls should be cut in half.)
Spread ham, then cheese. Cover with foil.
Cook 20 minutes on 200°.
If frozen, cook 1 hour on 200°.
Good to make and freeze.
Pull out later.

title: dorothy lynch salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whip.

title: trail mix
directions: Remove stems from seedless grapes.
Wash and drain.
Place in freezer.
Enjoy as a low calorie snack.
Tastes like a miniature Slurpee.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and sugars.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in
flour,
baking soda and salt.	Stir in chocolate chips. Place
on a cookie sheet (walnut size spoons) and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add alternately sifted dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions; pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured dish.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: boiled shrimp
directions: In a large, heavy stockpot, combine crab and shrimp boil, lemons, bay leaves, cayenne, 3 tablespoons salt, peppercorns and enough water to fill the pot 2/3 full.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to low.
Simmer 20 minutes to develop flavor.
Bring back to a boil.
Add shrimp.
Stir in quickly.
Cook just until all shrimp turn coral pink, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain immediately.
While shrimp are cooking, combine 2 gallons water and 2 tablespoons salt in sink with stopper in place.
Stir to dissolve salt; add ice cubes.
Place drained shrimp in ice bath; let stand until shrimp are well chilled, about 10 minutes.
Drain and refrigerate it not using at once.

title: bourbon sauce
directions: For best flavor use real butter.
Mix butter, sugar and water in saucepan and heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture very hot but not boiling.
Gradually pour some hot mixture into the egg, beating as you do so.
Pour egg mixture into remaining hot mixture, continuing to beat.
Let cool and add bourbon to taste.

title: kalikenney
directions: Cook cabbage in a small amount of water until tender.
Peel, boil and mash potatoes with cream, salt, pepper and butter.
Stir cooked cabbage into creamed potatoes.
Cook the bacon until crisp and after dicing, add to the cabbage and potato mixture along with the cheese.
Put in a casserole and bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Spray frying pan or wok with butter flavor Pam.
Quickly saute over medium-high heat the cubed chicken meat; add some water (1/4 cup) to bring up flavor.
After chicken is just about done, remove and set aside in covered dish.
Re-spray pan.
Over medium heat, add onion and green pepper; when onion is partially cooked, add broccoli.
Cover, heat and add 1/4 to 1/2 cup of chicken broth and season to taste.
When those vegetables are tender-crisp, add pea pods and sliced mushrooms, continue sauteing.
Stir 1 teaspoon cornstarch and remaining broth (water can be used or added for more juices); set aside.
Add chicken; saute some more to heat and mix thoroughly.
Add cornstarch mix.
Turn off heat and serve over 2/3 cup rice.
Each serving:
325 calories (including rice), 2 gm. fat.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 55 minutes, divided.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; whip until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and spices and stir together thoroughly.
Add pumpkin and water to sugar mixture, then spoon in dry ingredients.
Mix by hand until just moist.
Pour into greased bread pans and bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 4 to 5 loaves.

title: garlic flank steak
directions: Score flank steak on both sides.
Place meat in plastic bag; set in a bowl.
For marinade, in a bowl combine vinegar, water, Worcestershire sauce, cooking oil, garlic and red pepper.
Pour over meat in bag.
Place in refrigerator 4 to 24 hours.
Preheat broiler.
Meanwhile, place meat on rack in broiler pan.
Boil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Brush with marinade.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes more.
Place on platter.
Thinly slice meat diagonally across grain.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains 185 calories.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread beans into a 1-quart microwave bowl to cover bottom. Layer the remaining ingredients over beans in order given. Microwave until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Blend instant pudding mix and milk.
Spread over 1st layer.
Chill and serve.

title: hawaiian butterscotch cookies
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Pour onto waxed paper.
Add baking powder and salt to flour.
Stir to blend.
Cream sugar, butter and oleo thoroughly.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips, pineapple, nuts and orange rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonfuls onto well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet.
Cool on a rack.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown
meat
in
butter; add onion, water, tomatoes and salt. Cover;
simmer
for
30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add
peas and
noodles;
cook for 10 minutes, stirring often. More seasoning may be added if desired.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 1 tablespoon of butter and brown sugar.
Add salt to taste. Shape into 12 balls.
Combine crushed corn flakes and melted butter in shallow dish.
Roll balls in corn flake mixture.
Place about 2-inches apart in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples, flour, sugar and spice together.
Blend well. Place mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Add dots of butter and milk. Put on top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie.

title: tater tot casserole(from the files of charlie mae williams)
directions: Cook beef; drain and put in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixed with milk over meat.
Put layer of Velveeta on beef.
Put cooked Tater Tots over cheese.
Heat in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey's "kiss" cookies
directions: Beat butter with confectioners sugar. Add vanilla.
At low speed, add flour and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Divide into 40 or more pieces. Insert 1 Kiss on dough and cover completely with dough. Bake on ungreased sheet for 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool thoroughly. Roll cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Crust:
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly. Pat 1/3 of dough on bottom of 9-inch cheesecake pan.
(If you use 9-inch spring-form pan, it will leak butter.)
Remove sides.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown. Cool, attach sides to bottom and butter.
Pat remaining dough on sides to height of 1 3/4-inches.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake and cut into half.
Place one half in bottom of large bowl (punch bowl can be used).
Spread one can pudding mix over cake; add lots of Heath bars.
Spread part of Cool Whip on top of this.
Add second half of cake, then second can of chocolate pudding and more crushed Heath bars and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle some crushed Heath bars on top.
Use large spoon to serve.

title: mexican cheese
directions: Substitute mashed potatoes for egg yolks in your favorite recipe.
If you are using instant mashed potatoes, use about half of the water called for.

title: seafood thermidor(total cooking time:  15 to 18 minutes)
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
In 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole, place onion, bouillon, lemon juice, dill weed and water.
Cook, covered, on high (Maximum power) 2 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Add fish.
Cook, uncovered, on High (Maximum power) 2 minutes or until opaque.
Remove fish with slotted spoon and set aside.
Discard poaching mixture.

title: meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into twenty 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Place in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until no longer pink inside.

title: english muffins
directions: Scald
milk
and cool to lukewarm.
Add melted shortening, sugar
and
salt.
Dissolve
crumbled
yeast in lukewarm water and add to first mixture.
Add flour to make a moderately
soft dough.
Mix
well.
Remove to lightly floured board. Knead
until smooth.
Place
dough
in
greased
bowl.
Cover tightly.
Let rise in warm place until almost doubled.
Remove dough
to
a lightly
floured
board.
Flatten
to remove gas bubbles
and form into a roll.
Grease muffin rings and place on
a
greased pan.
Cut
off pieces of dough large enough to fill rings 1/3 full.
Put
dough
in
rings
and
flatten out. Cover and allow to rise
in
warm place until rings are about 3/4 full.
Or roll out
dough about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with floured cookie cutter. Let rise until light.
Bake on lightly greased griddle that is not
too
hot.
Turn when browned and bake other side when cool, split open and toast then.

title: chocolate butterscotch drops
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt morsels over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts and Kellogg's Crispix cereal.
Drop by measured tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Yields 2 dozen drops.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Combine water, butter, broccoli that has been chopped, onion and pepper in a 3-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in soup, then milk and cheese last.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheese melts and serving temperature is reached.
Do not boil.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti.
Drain and place in bowl of cold water; set aside.
Set oven at 350°.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, egg and egg white, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Drain manicotti.
Pat dry with a paper towel.
Fill shells with the cheese spread.
Put 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce over bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Arrange filled manicotti on sauce. Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses.
Cover dish loosely with foil.
Bake 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place the chicken breasts on a broiler pan and brush butter on the top of each.
Broil for 7 minutes at 500°.
Turn over and repeat with butter.
Remove chicken from broiler and brush the Dijon mustard on top of each breast.
Return to oven and bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

Remove chicken from oven and place one slice of cheese and one slice of ham on top of each chicken breast. Return to oven and bake for 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Turn off oven during the cheese melting.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Serves 4.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix
all
together.
Use two heaping spoonfuls for each cup of water.
Store in airtight jar.

title: mud brownies
directions: Melt margarine, stir in cocoa.
In large bowl beat eggs slightly on medium speed of mixer.
Add sugar, flour and margarine/cocoa mixture on medium speed until thoroughly blended. Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool before icing.

title: pierogi
directions: Cook peeled and cubed potatoes in water until soft.
Drain water, but save for dough.
Mash potatoes and add 2 cups of dry cottage cheese and 1/2 cup sauteed onions.
Mix together and refrigerate to cool.

title: bananas hawaiian
directions: Heat coconut in large skillet until brown; remove to a sheet of foil to cool.
Add butter, sugar, rum and cinnamon to skillet. Heat until bubbly.
Add bananas; cook until slices are heated thoroughly.
Spoon ice cream into serving dishes and spoon hot bananas and juice over ice cream.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serve at once.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili fiesta
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add spices, beans, tomato sauce and enchilada sauce.
Place in large greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and enough Fritos to cover.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in margarine.
Add all ingredients to beans.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour and pepper.
In skillet brown chicken in butter.
Stir in soup, water and oregano.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef vinnie
directions: Quickly brown cubed or sirloin steak in 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add garlic during last 30 seconds of browning. Add liquid ingredients and seasonings. Simmer 30 minutes. The last 5 minutes, add 1/4 pound fresh sliced mushrooms and garnish with 2 green onions. Serve with side dish of pasta.
Cover pasta with meat, juices, green onions and mushrooms.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with onion rings and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soup and Veg-All.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Place second pie shell on top and seal edges.
Make slit in top to vent.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffing good chicken
directions: Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay cheese over chicken.
Mix soup and wine with whisk and pour over chicken. Add cheese.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use for dip for pumpernickel bread or vegetables.

title: michelle's sour cream cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over the 1/4 batter in pan.
Add remaining batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach wow
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and garlic.
Add spinach, salt, garlic powder, sour cream, artichokes, cheeses and mushrooms. Stir.
Place in a casserole.
Top with more grated Parmesan cheese and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: aunt ruth's jello dessert
directions: Add the oranges to the first 3 ingredients when it begins to set.

title: crawfish fettucine
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add half and half and water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Add crawfish, Parmesan cheese and all seasonings; stir well. Toss with fettucine.

title: egg salad filling
directions: Stir
together
all of the ingredients until well mixed. Makes 2 cups.
Enough for 6 sandwiches.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add onion and saute. Mash squash and add to meat.
Stir small amount of meat mixture into eggs to prevent eggs from cooking.
Stir into meat mixture in skillet.
Add bread crumbs and some cheese.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: triple cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Slightly thaw broccoli so it will break apart easily; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients; add broccoli and stir until well mixed.
Pour into shallow ungreased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onions in water until almost tender; drain water.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix 1 teaspoon flour with 1/4 cup warm water.
Add in pan with milk on top of other ingredients.
Cook to boil, then simmer until thick.
Serve with bread or crackers of choice.

title: graham gems or muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake in muffin tins in 350° oven.

title: chocolate pretzel dessert
directions: Melt milk chocolate flavored disks, the white chocolate flavored disks and the peanut butter in the microwave.
Melt on Defrost for 1 minute, then check every 10 seconds until melted. Stir in 2 cups of crushed pretzels (I used pretzel sticks, which I put in a sealed plastic bag and crushed with a rolling pin.
I left some chunks for crunch.)
Spread on cookie sheet really thin; refrigerate.
When set, break up in small pieces to serve.

title: norwegian cream cake(blotkake)
directions: Beat yolks and water until thick; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff. Fold cake flour, which has been sifted with salt, alternately with egg mixture into the whites.
Bake in 2 layers (ungreased pans) in a 325° oven for 25 minutes.
When cake is cool, split each layer to make 4 layers.

title: medley of rice salad
directions: Cook rice per package directions; omit addition of butter. Drain as directed.
Place rice, while still hot, in a bowl large enough for mixing all ingredients.
Coat hot rice very well with Italian dressing.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Toss well. Next, add onions and celery.
While rice cools, chop olives and chestnuts.
Mix mayo and sauce.
Add to rice mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Add apples, pecans and dry ingredients to oil mixture; mix well.
Bake in stem pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and Velveeta together; mix into vegetables.
Melt 1/4 stick margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: zucchini veggie
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Cut in oleo until crumbly. Pat half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cook zucchini and lemon juice until tender.
Add 2 cups sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Simmer 4 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of mix into zucchini.
Stir well until it thickens.
Then pour filling onto crust.
Sprinkle rest of flour mixture over filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nutt house buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat in the eggs and flour until fluffy.
Fold in the buttermilk and add the nutmeg and/or vanilla or lemon extract.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat together eggs, salt, sugar, vanilla, oil and buttermilk. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into muffin pans and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and flatten slightly with fingers.
Place on ungreased baking sheet that has been lined with parchment.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While warm, dust generously with confectioners sugar.
Cool, then dust with sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pork chops with savory sauce
directions: Combine flour and seasoned salt.
Coat chops with flour mixture.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chops and brown on each side.
Arrange onion rings on top of chops.
Add broth; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir in sour cream and milk; cook until hot.
Do not boil.
Serve over Parsley Rice.

title: grandma dague's chocolate cake
directions: Mix until creamy the sugar and butter.
Add cocoa and blend. Add buttermilk, then boiling water.
Next add eggs, flour, vanilla and soda.
Place in cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter, combine all ingredients cook over low heat until potatoes are tender.

title: rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a blender; let stand for 15 minutes. Then, add next 3 ingredients.
In a large bowl measure 3 cups pre-sifted flour and add blended ingredients; mix well.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Flour a flat surface generously; knead dough until no sticky surface shows.
Roll; cut with a floured cutter.
Place close together in a greased pan.
Let rise for 45 minutes or longer if room isn't warm.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dutch oven roast
directions: In a
Dutch
oven,
place
bacon
on
bottom.
Sprinkle seasoning salt all over meat; don't be shy.
Pour in V-8 juice and 1/2 can
beer (add more beer if needed).
Place onions and carrots around
meat.
Cook
at
or simmer until meat is almost tender.
Add
potatoes
and continue cooking until meat and potatoes
are done.
This usually makes its own gravy, but you may have to add some more liquid as needed.

title: almond horns
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add butter and work into flour until well mixed. Add the almonds and lemon extract.
Take small amounts of crumbs and roll in palm of hand until smooth. Make them long and form into horn shape.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let them cool completely, then roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 12 dozen crescents.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, butter or margarine and 1 whipped egg well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease two loaf pans (9-inch).
Peel and remove seeds of zucchini and grate.
Beat eggs until fluffy and add all other ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Add nuts last.
Turn into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool before cutting.
Freezes well.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
whipped topping, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour
in
pie
crust.
Garnish with topping of your choice, fruit, nuts, graham cracker crumbs or whipped topping. Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.

title: chicken sausage gumbo
directions: Brown chicken in some fat in large iron pot.
Remove chicken from pot.
Add remainder of fat and flour, stirring constantly, until brown.
Add celery, onions and bell pepper.
Saute, stirring occasionally, until it begins to separate.
Add cold water all at once.
Bring to rapid boil.
Add chicken*.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add sausage.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add parsley and green onions when chicken is cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: luscious layered torte
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Cool and split each layer to make 4 layers.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except the Fritos and dressing. Just before
serving,
add the dressing and toss.
Add Fritos last to prevent sogginess.	Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Blend shrimp on chop setting.
Add other ingredients and mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Slice potatoes in baking dish.
Pat out ground beef; place on potatoes, then put vegetables over ground beef.
Put some margarine (1/2 stick) over vegetables and add 1/2 cup of water. Seal with aluminum foil airtight.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine the cornmeal and salt in a small mixing bowl.
Stir in boiling water and set the mixture aside to cool.

Divide the mixture into 8 portions and shape each portion into a cake. Heat the drippings in a heavy skillet until hot, but not smoking. Add the cakes and fry over medium heat about 15 minutes, turning to brown both sides.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice over the bottom of baking pan (ungreased). Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of rice.
Arrange pieces of chicken in single layers.
Combine mushroom soup and water; mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° until chicken is tender (about 35 to 50 minutes).

title: delightful dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine and combine with flour and pecans.
Mix well and pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes; let cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup nondairy whipped topping.
Spread evenly over baked crust.
Combine instant pudding mixes with 2 cups milk, according to package directions.
Spread pudding mixture evenly over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining nondairy whipped topping over pudding layer.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Yields 16 squares.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in a skillet. Drain grease off and put in a large bowl.
Add taco seasoning, cream-style corn and kidney beans (rinse before adding).
In a 13 x 9-inch cake pan, line the bottom with crushed Doritos.
Add mixture from bowl and spread across the pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover the pan with crushed Doritos.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with taco sauce or salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jelly roll
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until lemon color.
In small bowl, mix 1 cup cake flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Sift together, then put in egg mixture.
Set aside.
Now, beat egg whites until real stiff. Beat until stiff enough to hold peaks, then fold in egg mixture with flour.
Put on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn upside down on powdered sugar dusted towel.
Take off foil and roll up.
When cool, put jelly or jam on it.

title: mincemeat bread
directions: Combine mincemeat and egg in large bowl; blend thoroughly. Stir in cinnamon, honey and water.
Add nut bread.
Mix all at once and stir.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan 10 minutes after baking.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: date coffee cake
directions: Beat together bananas and butter until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla extract and water; beat. Add all the rest and beat well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Soften butter or margarine. Mix all ingredients well. Pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: holiday corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Set aside. Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Fill muffin cups to 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Add chicken livers, undrained mushrooms, salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover; cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Mix flour with sour cream. Stir into liver mixture.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Butter bottom of dish with margarine. Tear flour tortilla up and put on the bottom of dish. Spread refried beans on

tortillas. Brown meat and mix with taco seasoning (package). Put meat on top of bean layer. Take cream of chicken, mix with Ro-Tel. Pour over meat. Put shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: pork chops with apricot glaze
directions: In small saucepan, combine apricot spread, wine, mustard, honey and ginger. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture is smooth and thickened, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat; cover and keep warm.

title: summertime pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Place in a 14 x 10-inch pan, flatten and pinch seams together.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden.
Cool.

Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on crust. Top with any combination of finely chopped vegetables (green pepper, tomatoes, broccoli and cauliflower). Cover with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with dill weed. Serve cold.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients together for 1 minute.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add applesauce; mix well. Add water alternately with dry ingredients.
Add raisins; pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease well 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake upright at 350° for one hour or until done.
Release from cans and set upright on rack to cool.
After cooling, bread can be wrapped and frozen.

title: creamed party potatoes
directions: One hour before baking, put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan (2-quart).
Combine soup, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and Cheddar cheese.
As potatoes thaw, stir this mix into potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: scotcheroos
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar and syrup; bring just to a boil over moderate heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt the chips in a double boiler.
Spread over top of cereal mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until firm (about 15 minutes).

title: easy shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp or fish.
Microwave on High 8 to 12 minutes; stir once.
Stir in shrimp or fish.
Cover; microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Let stand 5 minutes. May be served over rice.
Serves 4.
Contains 141 calories.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour with salt.
Add Crisco; mix with spoon.
Add milk; blend in with hands.
Chill in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Roll on floured board or table.
Makes enough for 2 crust pie.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes for a single crust shell.

title: martin warner's chocolate icing
directions: In a pan big enough for a big boil over direct heat, heat sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 1 minute under full heat, then turn flame very low.
Add chocolate chips.
Melt chocolate.
Whisk out lumps.

title: cherry-cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Press evenly over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been previously well-greased. Sprinkle coconut over the first layer, then chocolate chips, then nuts.
Drizzle evenly over the sweetened condensed milk until covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into 24 squares. Cool completely before storing tightly in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: fresh fruit medley with frosty melon dressing
directions: In small saucepan combine orange juice and gelatin; let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved; set aside.
In a blender or food processor bowl, blend the cantaloupe, honey, vinegar and cinnamon until smooth.
Add orange juice mixture, process until combined.
Transfer melon mixture to an 8 x 4 x 2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover; freeze for 4 hours.
Break frozen mixture into small chunks. Transfer melon mixture to a chilled mixing bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed until blended; but not melted.
Rinse and dry the pan; line with plastic wrap.
Return mixture to loaf pan.
Cover and freeze until firm for up to 2 weeks.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: In large bowl with fork, combine mayonnaise, vinegar and salt. Add chicken and remaining ingredients, except romaine.
Toss well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted margarine in bottom of a glass dish.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, 10x sugar, vanilla and 1 stick margarine; spread over crust, then put crushed pineapple.
Then slice bananas over this.
Then add Cool Whip on top.
Then drizzle chocolate syrup over and dot with cherries and coconut.
Chill.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts (thaw).
Heat margarine over low heat. Blend in flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until bubbly and smooth.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling for about 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and vegetables.
Place first crust on bottom and up sides of 8 x 8-inch glass Pyrex dish.
Pour in mixture and place second crust on top. Pinch edges closed.
Cook uncovered at 425° or until crust is brown for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water for 30 minutes.
Mix together cornflakes (crushed by hand) and melted margarine.
Place in bottom of large baking dish.
Put cabbage on top of mixture and salt to taste.
Make a sauce of mayonnaise, milk and celery soup.
Heat and pour over cabbage.
Top with shredded cheese and cornflakes.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine
all
together and cook slowly for 2 hours.
If you don't like it hot, use 3/4 bottle of Texas Pete.

title: summer's salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine everything except dressing. Add dressing and gently toss.

title: wendy's overnight layered green salad
directions: Shred lettuce and put in 4 qt. serving dish. Top with green onions and water-chestnuts. Break apart frozen peas, sprinkle over salad. Spread mayonnaise evenly over top. Sprinkle sugar, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder over the top. Cover and chill 24 hours. Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon, eggs, and olives. Add tomato wedges.

title: almond puff
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture and mix with a fork.
Round into a ball and divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into strips, 12 x 3-inches.
Strips should be about 3-inches apart.

title: homemade white bread(one loaf)
directions: Pour water into a very warm bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over the water, stirring until yeast is dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons salad oil, again stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add 1 1/2 cups of the flour.
Beat well. Stir in remaining flour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large Dutch oven; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well; rinse with cold water.
Chill. Peel and devein shrimp.
Set aside 1 pound of shrimp; reserve the rest for other uses.
Saute onion and green pepper in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add tomatoes and next 8 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally (sauce will be thick).
Remove from heat; discard bay leaf.
Stir in shrimp.

title: simple and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Make into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Smash with a fork to cross cookies.
Bake for 7 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: marble squares(the winner cake at 1988 reunion)
