directions: Combine softened cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar; mix well, until blended.
Add 1 egg; mix well.
Combine margarine, water and unsweetened chocolate in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and 2 cups sugar.
Add 2 eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over chocolate mixture.
Cut through batter with knife for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cut into squares.

title: cheddar chicken and mushrooms
directions: Coat chicken with bread crumbs and brown lightly on both sides in medium skillet with oil.
Layer chicken in medium casserole dish.
Spread undiluted mushroom soup over chicken.
Top with fresh sliced mushrooms and cheese. Cover and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add all ingredients, except beets and cucumbers; chill until partially set.
Add the beets and cucumbers; chill in individual molds.
Serves 8.

title: taco rice
directions: Fry ground beef; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning, dry rice, water and seasonings.
Bring to boil; turn down to lowest setting.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cheese.
Serve in flour tortillas or plain.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix together and churn freeze.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix together.
Place in a serving dish.
Top with relish and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: apple upside-down cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: glazed beef loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, catsup and mustard.
Spread over loaf and continue baking for 15 more minutes.

title: anyone can yeast rolls
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Separate flaky biscuits into two layers.
Spread small amount of cream cheese mixture on biscuits to within 1/4 inch of edge of biscuits. Press the biscuit edges together to seal.

title: best-ever oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine
oats and buttermilk in a large
bowl
and
let stand 1
hour.
Add egg, sugar and oil;
mix
well.
Combine remaining ingredients except raisins in a medium bowl.
Add to oats mixture,
stirring
just to moisten.
Stir
in
raisins. Spoon into muffin pans, either greased or papered, filling 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 18 minutes. Yields 18 muffins.

title: cranberry glaze
directions: Mix and cook first 4 ingredients slowly.
Add cornstarch and water.
Cook until thickened.
Add to ham last 30 minutes of baking (Cure 8 or Bryan Centerpiece).

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until both are well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until well coated.
Press into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes until very thick.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with nuts.

title: ziti bake
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In 8-quart Dutch oven, prepare ziti as label directs; drain.
Set aside.
In same Dutch oven, over medium-high heat; cook ground beef until well browned, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove Dutch oven from heat; stir in Ricotta, next 5 ingredients and half of spaghetti sauce until well mixed.
Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking pan; pour remaining spaghetti sauce evenly over ziti mixture; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: In large pan, put bread flour with salt.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon flavor, then add flour.
Heat together skim milk and butter or margarine until butter melts.
Mix together yeast, warm water and sugar until it starts to act.
Add all ingredients to flour; mix well and fold until well mixed.
Let rest 20 minutes.
Fold again and let rest 20 minutes 2 more times.
Put in warm nondrafty place.
Cover with towel and blanket over.
Let rise 4 hours.
Put in pans and let rise 2 more hours.
Bake at 275° to 300° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Brush tops with egg yolk and milk when almost time to come out of the oven, then put back in the oven until dry.
Put on racks and let cool.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Cook grits and water until thick, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in margarine, grated cheese, salt and seasoning.
Stir in egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Mash bananas and add to mixture. Add nuts and flour, then pour into a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine milk, Bisquick mix, sugar and softened margarine until smooth.
Pour half of ingredients into baking dish.
Pour cherry pie filling into dish.
Add remaining batter.
Sprinkle with Topping.

title: angel food delight
directions: Soften cream cheese and add sugar.
Add milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Crumble cake into bite-size and add in mixtures.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan, topping with pie filling.
Toasted pecans may be used on top of Cool Whip mixture.

title: banana berry smoothie
directions: In a blender, process all the ingredients until combined. Serve immediately.
Makes 1 1/2 cup servings.

title: tuna tarragon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set for at least 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers or on bread as finger sandwiches.

title: gorilla bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray. Mix the granulated sugar and cinnamon. In a saucepan melt the butter and brown sugar over low heat, stirring well; set aside. Cut the cream cheese into 20 equal cubes. Press the biscuits out with your fingers and sprinkle each with 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon sugar. Place a cube of cream cheese in the center of each biscuit, wrapping and sealing the dough around the cream cheese. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of nuts into the bottom of the bundt pan. Place half of the prepared biscuits in the pan. Sprinkle

with cinnamon sugar, pour half of the melted butter mixture over the biscuits, and sprinkle on 1/2 cup of nuts. Layer the remaining biscuits on top, sprinkle with the remaining cinnamon sugar, pour the remaining butter mixture over the biscuits, and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup of nuts. Bake for 50 minutes. Remove from the oven and
cool for 5 minutes. Place a plate on top and invert.

title: spaghetti pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti al dente.
Rinse in cold water and drain well. Put everything into a large bowl and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti with broccoli
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth used to boil chicken breasts. Drain.
Cook broccoli for approximately 4 minutes and drain. Combine soup, milk, broth and cheese and let melt over low heat. Place broccoli over bottom of
9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add a portion of the sauce, then spaghetti.
Add chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour remaining sauce over all.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 5 to 8 people.

title: hot cider
directions: Mix water, cider, orange juice, lemonade and sugar together. Place spices in the coffee basket.
Pour the mixture into the coffeemaker and brew until done.

title: puffed shrimp and cheese sandwiches
directions: In small heavy saucepan, melt butter over moderate heat.
Add scallions and mushrooms and saute until golden and soft, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in egg yolks, cheese, dry mustard, dill and shrimp.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into shrimp mixture.
Spread an equal portion of mixture on one side of each toasted bread slice.
Sprinkle evenly with paprika and arrange on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 minutes or until puffy.
Serve hot or cold.

title: japanese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add dry ingredients.
Shape dough into 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm. Slice 1/4-inch thick; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: butterscotch nut pie
directions: In saucepan, heat milk until bubbles form around sides of pan, set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Gradually add sugar, flour and salt and stir until smooth.
Add hot milk, stirring with wire whisk.
Cook until mixture begins to boil, boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: chicken livers and rice dish
directions: Saute chicken livers and mushrooms in butter in a large skillet for 5 to 8 minutes or until livers are brown.
Remove livers and mushrooms from skillet; set aside.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Butter the bread on one side (outside) and with pizza sauce on the inside.
Sprinkle some shredded cheese on the pizza sauce side. Place some pepperoni on the cheese and cover with some more cheese.
Place the other slice on top and grill on the stove like a melted cheese sandwich.
Serve with some chips.
Yields 1 serving.

title: peach butterscotch crisp
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the peaches, thoroughly. Place peaches in baking dish and top with the dry mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: magic pie crust
directions: Melt margarine in a Pyrex dish; mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into Pyrex dish; then add any fruit (peaches work very well) on top of the pie crust mixture.
Crust will rise to the top as it bakes.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: one cup casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles and place a layer of noodles, a layer of corned beef and then onions in a baking dish.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and paprika.
Bake 20 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: hot onion-cream cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Stir together the onions, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise until well combined. Transfer to a 2-quart souffl dish. Bake about 15 minutes or until the top is golden brown. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: james' sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (if too dry, add milk). Spoon small mixtures on greased cookie pan. Cook at 300° for 10 or 15 minutes or until golden around the edges.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt oleo and add flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: almond fruited cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, raisins, coconut, pineapple, almond extract and half of the crushed cereal.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Form into ball.
Just before serving, roll in 1/4 cup crushed cereal.
Serve with crackers and fruit.

title: cookie pie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg.
Add flour, soda mixture, spices and salt.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Put in a greased, deep 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Can be served warm or cold and with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
I like it warm.
"Good cooking."

title: spicy vegetable beef soup
directions: Saute beef, onion and garlic, then drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are cooked.

title: hodgepodge
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly warm.
Serve with either crackers, corn chips or cornbread.
May sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: The day before serving, in a large bowl, combine gelatin and boiling water.
Stir to dissolve gelatin.
Stir in strawberries until they are thawed.
Stir bananas and pineapple into gelatin. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Just before serving, spread with sour cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine in 250° oven in large roasting pans.
When melted, stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Now pour in all cereals, nuts, pretzels and crackers.
Mix thoroughly until all pieces are coated.
Then put pan back in oven and bake for 1 hour. Let cool and store in airtight containers.
Makes about 9 cups mix.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine veggies, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour in casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In saucepan melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Add rice.
Stir until rice is coated with butter.
Add broth; bring mixture to a boil.
Turn heat down; cover.
Simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring after the first 15 minutes to distribute vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes
in large casserole.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut green pepper in half.
Remove seeds and core.
Place ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Stuff peppers.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour some sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Do not open oven until time is up.

title: classic quiche lorraine
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan with pastry; trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of shell with a fork and bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool on wire rack. Sprinkle bacon and cheese evenly into pastry shell.
Combine eggs, half and half, salt and pepper; mix well and pour into shell.
Bake the quiche at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 40 minutes or until set.
Yields one 9-inch quiche.

title: chili conqueso dip
directions: Heat chilies, tomato, onion and hot sauce on medium heat until soft; add cubed cheese and cook at medium heat until melted. Serve with tortilla chips or similar dip product.

title: layered grapes
directions: Mix whipping cream, dressing, walnuts and sugar.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Layer mixture with grapes in crystal parfait glasses. Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend with egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Turn into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan with nonstick spray.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg and eggs.
Pour into pan. Pour dry cake mix over the mixture.
Pat nuts evenly into dry mixture.
Spoon melted butter or margarine evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Can be served with Cool Whip on top or plain. Refrigerate leftover cake.
Yields 24 small servings.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix ground beef and ingredients for rolls.
Cook cabbage and separate.
Roll beef mixture into balls and put into cabbage leaves.
Mix sauce ingredients all together.
Layer cabbage rolls, sauerkraut and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: fondue hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except franks in a large pot.
Simmer; add franks.
Continue simmering on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple salad
directions: Bring to a boil pineapple and sugar.
Add jello.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease a large cookie sheet. In top of double boiler, combine condensed milk, chocolate and salt; cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, until chocolate melts and mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls, 1 inch apart, on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or just until cookies are set.
Transfer at once to wire rack to cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas together.
Bananas must be whipped and added last.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Test before removing from oven.

title: hot crabmeat sandwiches(open faced)
directions: Toast bread slices. Mix enough mayonnaise with crabmeat to moisten.
Add Lawry's seasoned salt.
Spread on toasted bread.
Top with thin tomato slices and bacon which has been partially cooked. Put under broiler until heated through and bacon has finished cooking.

title: mushroom rice pilaf
directions: Put water and broth in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add rice and cover, simmering for 20 minutes.
While rice is cooking, saute mushrooms, celery and onions until tender in a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Combine cooked rice and mushroom mixture. Then serve.

title: patsy's chicken
directions: Put all ingredients together in crock-pot or oven pan and cook overnight or until tender.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into 1-inch chunks.
Place them in a saucepan with leeks, celery, carrot and butter.
Add salt.
Cook the vegetables, stirring over medium heat, until butter is melted and all is coated (5 minutes).
Add stock or water; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until potatoes are soft (20 to 30 minutes).
Check moisture level; you may need to add more water or stock.
When potatoes are tender, remove the pan from heat and puree its contents in the milk (use a blender or food processor).
Make sure mixture is smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Add optional herbs (or not).
Grind in black pepper and salt to taste.
Heat soup gently, covered, until just hot.
Try not to boil.
Serve immediately.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Dice very finely the tomatoes, cucumbers and onion.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Makes very large quantity.
If your family does not care for cucumbers, substitute yellow squash or broccoli.

title: mound cake
directions: Mix as directed on box.
Bake in layer pan.

title: quick cheese and bacon corn bread
directions: Empty the corn muffin mix into a bowl and stir in the cheese and bacon.
Add the egg and milk, according to the directions on the package mix, and the butter flavoring.

title: creamed baby onions
directions: To make peeling of onions easier, place them in a pot of boiling water and cook for 2 minutes.
Drain and peel.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add warm milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook 3 minutes longer.
Add seasonings and onions.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce with gelatin until soupy.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and stir in dressing.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Measure and pour ingredients into a large bowl as listed. Stir with wooden spoon only until blended. Be sure to scrape off bottom of bowl. Bake in grease pan (angel food cake pan, large Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans). Bake on lowest rack of oven at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until top of cake is deep brown, shiny, with cracks forming.
Cool completely in pan, then loosen sides. Freezes well!
Tastes even better on second day.

title: peach crisp
directions: Pour fruit in a long Pyrex dish and mix all dry ingredients together and then add the beaten egg.
It will be crumbly. Sprinkle over fruit and pour melted butter over this.
Then sprinkle a little cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar on the top.
Place in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Other fruits besides peaches may be used.

title: italian meatball sandwich casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix and knead like bread dough.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Knead again, refrigerate again and knead again.
Do this again for 1 more day (3 days total).
On the fourth day, form into 4 logs.

title: lemon cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, margarine and nuts until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 8 x 8-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and carrots until tender.
Blend flour, paprika, chicken cubes and dry mustard.
Gradually stir in milk and water. Stir until thick and mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese.

title: frog eye saladfort collins, colorado
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler until thick, 8 minutes or longer.

title: grandma ella's dewberry pie
directions: Pour dewberries
into
unbaked
pie shell.
Mix rest of ingredients together
and
pour over berries.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef in sour cream
directions: Spread noodles in 2-quart casserole. Add remaining ingredients. Stir, cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; beat
in sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins and walnuts. Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Raisins and walnuts are optional.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into
an ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool 30 minutes before serving.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Place apples and water in a large pan.
Cover and cook over medium heat 30-40 minutes or until apples are tender, remove from heat.
Using a potato masher, mash apples to desired consistency. Stir in cinnamon and sweetener.

title: amish slaw
directions: Let stand in refrigerator for a day.
Will keep for as long as you like.

title: marinated green bean salad
directions: Combine
vegetables.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and
pepper.
Pour over bean mixture.
Marinate, stirring often. Store in icebox 4 to 6 hours.

title: mexican nut cookies
directions: Beat margarine until creamy.
Add sugar, mixing until light. Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan while still warm and roll cookies in additional powdered sugar.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies in halves.
Place half of them in casserole dish or cake pan, side by side, filling side up.
Prepare pudding and pie filling according to package directions.
Pour over Twinkies.
Place the other half of the Twinkies on top with the filling side down.
Pour strawberries over this.
Serve with dollops of whipped cream or you can spread the whipped cream over the dessert in the pan.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: emmaues dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Cream shortening with sugar, add eggs. Combine sifted measured flour with salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add cocoa paste.
If using electric mixer, remove mixer blades, fold in vinegar and soda.
Pour batter in equal portions into 3 (8-inch) cake pans, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter or margarine until light and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Combine plain flour, baking powder and salt.
Add about 1/4 of flour and 1/4 of milk until all is used, beating well on low speed after each addition.
Add flavorings and coconut.
Bake in tube pan sprayed with Pam at 300° to 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Squash potatoes into a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Heat bacon grease or about 4 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Place mixture in skillet and brown to golden on bottom. Use cover.
Turn over to serve.

title: nine-day cabbage salad
directions: Bring to a boil first five ingredients.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage, pepper and onion rings.
Keep mixture well covered with the liquid.

title: chili pot roast
directions: Rub beef with mixture of flour, salt, cumin and chili powder. Heat oil in deep, heavy, nonstick Dutch oven.
Add beef.
Brown over medium heat on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Pour off any excess fat.
Turn heat to lowest setting.
Add tomato juice or broth.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour, adding water if liquid boils down too dry.
Place whole cauliflower on top of beef. Cover and cook over lowest heat 30 minutes.
Add broccoli to the pot.
Cook over lowest heat 30 minutes longer.
At the end of this time, the cauliflower and broccoli will be slowly steamed to tender crispness.
If vegetables cook too quickly (your range may keep a higher heat than others, even at lowest setting), remove them and reheat to serve.

title: roast chicken
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Blend chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Layer rice, broccoli and chicken soup/cheese mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Great side dish or can be served with sea biscuits.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Cook chicken in hot oil about 2 minutes on each side and then set aside.
In same pan, cook onion, pepper and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Drain excess oil.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, broth, uncooked rice and pepper sauce.
Bring to boil and then remove from heat.
Spoon into baking dish and arrange chicken on top.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, uncovered, about 5 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: rolled tortillas
directions: Mix all but tortillas.
Spread on open tortillas.
Roll and chill.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Serve with picante.
These can be frozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in a skillet.
Add dash of salt, taco seasoning, tomatoes and corn.
Put in your casserole dish.
Mix cornbread as directed on package.
Spoon over your casserole as you wish.
Place in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cornbread is lightly browned.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: succotash
directions: Cook vegetables in small amount of salted water.
Drain excess liquid and combine with remaining ingredients.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Mix 1 cup of each together in a large bowl.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
The longer the better.

title: sweet n' sour ham rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter and add ham and onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Drain pineapple chunks and reserve liquid.
Add water to liquid to make 2 1/2 cups.

title: grandma nell's noodle recipe
directions: Double or triple for larger quantities.
Beat the egg in a bowl.
Mix in the vegetable oil and milk.
Add the dry ingredients and mix.
Work the dough into a ball and roll out thin.
Flour lightly.
Roll up the dough and cut off narrow strips.
Spread and allow to dry some.
Cook in boiling broth until tender.

title: ritz cookies(very rich; great finger food.)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add eggs, flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Put in fridge for 1 hour.
Roll thin, 1/4 inch. Sprinkle top with sugar.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix the cornstarch and milk, salt and corn.
Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add to corn mixture.
Add melted butter last. Put in a greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sunday stuffed bars
directions: Mix crab meat, stuffing and butter together.
Upon mixing, mixture should hold together enough to form a patty, but not be mushy.
Place three fillets in the bottom of a baking pan, sprayed with cooking spray.
Place stuffing mixture on top of each fillet, molding the stuffing patty to conform to the shape of the fillet.

title: wake-up special
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole with green pepper.
Saute in microwave oven 30 seconds.
Stir eggs and soup together.
Blend into sauteed mixture.
Cook in microwave 4 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrot salad
directions: Boil the water, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand for a few hours before serving.

title: mock champagne
directions: Combine equal parts of both.
Pour over ice and serve.

title: zucchini rolls with tomato sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium-low.
Add whole garlic cloves and cook until golden brown and soft (10 minutes).
Remove garlic.
Mash and set aside.
Add onion and saute.
Add tomatoes, salt and sugar.
Partially cover and cook until chunky sauce forms.
Remove from heat.
Add mashed garlic.

title: recipe for a great family cook
directions: Season with a dash of fun to taste and stir thoroughly.
Cook slowly until done.
(Or at least before your family distracts you and you burn it!)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Empty in large bowl and cut in bite sizes.
Add shredded cheese.
Add hot cooked rice and all soups.
Mix thoroughly and bake in 9 x 11-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: best moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed, starting with oleo and ending with hot water.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add water and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Allow cake to cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Drizzle with glaze of powdered sugar, lemon juice and butter.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter until brown.
Combine with soup, broth and chilies.
Add pieces of chicken and mix well.
Place layer of tortillas, layer of chicken mixture and layer of cheese in a large baking dish.
Repeat layers until dish is filled.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut pineapple log
directions: Save back 1 cup peanuts and combine all the other ingredients; refrigerate until firm.
Remove and shape into a log or ball and roll in the reserved peanuts.
Wrap loosely in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled; garnish with parsley and maraschino cherries.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Place drained hominy in a large, greased baking dish.
Mix soups, pimentos and peppers.
Mix part of cheese into mixture. Mix all together.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves about 20.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift together and set aside the flour and salt.
Combine and set aside the orange slice candy, chopped dates, walnuts or pecans and coconut.
(Important:
Add 1/2 cup flour mixture and mix well.)
Beat until light and fluffy the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine soda with buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture to the shortening mixture.
Add candy mixture. Blend in by hand with rubber spatula.
Put into 10-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: chocolate nut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Put 3 cups of chocolate chips and water into saucepan.
Place over low heat until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Place chocolate mixture into bowl.
Add applesauce and beat with electric mixer.
Add sugar and eggs until blended.
Beat in flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes until a toothpick inserted comes out moist, not wet.
Cool and cut into 24 squares.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburg, egg, chopped onion, bread crumbs and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Shake into 1-inch balls and bake on cookie sheets in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Put chili sauce and grape jelly into a crock-pot.
Mix well.
Add baked meatballs.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours or until ready to serve.

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in bowl and cover with sauce, salt and pepper. Cook slow in 300° oven, covered, until tender.

title: fried corn
directions: Combine corn, salt, pepper and green pepper; cook in fat about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: giant popover for two
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
While oven is heating up, place butter in 9-inch skillet or heavy casserole dish and melt in oven until bubbling.
Beat eggs with flour, milk and salt.
Pour into skillet or casserole dish.
Bake for 15 or 20 minutes, or until puffed and golden.
Serves 2.

title: strawberry milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender.
While blending, add 3 ice cubes at a time.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Take off fire; add quickly peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Stir all together until smooth.
Put out on greased cookie sheet.

title: egyptian stew
directions: Brown onions and peppers lightly in the oil.
Add the beans, corn and small amount of water and simmer 1/2 hour.
Then add zucchini, tomatoes, parsley and seasonings.
Cook very slowly for 45 minutes.
Add water when needed.

title: doughnuts and doughnut holes
directions: Use refrigerator biscuits.
Cut hole in center of each biscuit.
Deep fry in 365° oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel. Shake in bag of 1/2 cup sugar mixed with 1 tablespoon cinnamon while doughnut is still hot.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients with pastry blender.
Add egg and milk.
Press dough into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan and up on the sides a bit.
Place rhubarb into cake shell and sprinkle with Jell-O.

title: japanese steak
directions: In wok, steam onion and broccoli.
Remove and cook steak, adding both wine and seasoning.
Cook steak until medium well. Drain wok.
Add onion and broccoli; salt and pepper to taste. Makes 3 servings.

title: swiss potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done; peel and cut in chunks.
Add pimientos, olives, green onions, 8 slices cheese (cut in cubes) and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in oblong 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining slices of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease a large pan.
Break up 6 tortillas and lay in bottom of pan.
Take half olives, onions and cheese.
Layer on top of tortillas.
Pour half the sauce over and start all over with tortillas.
Do the same with the rest.
May make three layers if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Mix broth, soup and flavorings together.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup rice in large buttered casserole dish.
Pour soup mix over rice.
Dip chicken pieces in melted oleo.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Place in casserole.
Liquid should cover chicken.
If not, add a small amount of water.
Cook slowly (covered for a while) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: chunky garden gazpacho
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large mixing bowl and stir to mix well. Chill for at least 6 hours before serving. Yield: About 14 servings.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine cranberries, sugar and chopped walnuts.
Pour this into pie pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a saucepan.
Combine with cracker crumbs; press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat remaining margarine with powdered sugar and eggs for 15 minutes.
(Stop mixer off and on if it tends to overheat.) Pour mixture over cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas over this.
Top with pineapple and whipped topping.
Dot with cherries; sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate.
Better the second day.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Use self-rising flour and omit the baking powder, if so desired.
Mix
all	ingredients
together;	mix well.
Bake in 350° oven in
an
x
x
2-inch
pan or a loaf pan for 50 minutes.
It
will	rise,
but will fall as it is removed from the oven.
It will be waxy.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in large bowl.
Add cream cheese, onion, eggs and flour.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until ingredients are blended.
Then turn on high speed and beat until light and fluffy.
Taste and add salt and pepper as needed.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch baking casserole.
Sprinkle chip crumbs atop potatoes.
With knife, poke some of crumbs into potato mixture. Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: pepperoni dip(serve hot or cold)
directions: Mix all ingredients and warm in microwave. Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown onion and garlic in small amount of oil or butter.
Add meat and brown. Add kidney beans, catsup, chili powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with bay leaf and celery for 20 to 30 minutes, until done.
Save broth.
Cut up chicken.
Add 1/2 cup celery and onion; mix.
Mix Cool Whip and dressing; add to first mixture. Mix. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add grapes.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Can add slivered almonds or raisins.
Serves 8.

title: miracle banana pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Beat until thick.
Add a few spoons of Cool Whip to this mixture.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle a few crushed vanilla wafers on top.

title: fiesta chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in lime juice, garlic, chili powder and cumin for about 15 minutes.
Saute the chicken in the oil until done, then add the onion and pepper.
Stir in the salsa.
Spoon onto the tortillas and top with cheese.

title: ham pot pie
directions: Boil ham bone and onions for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Take bone out. Cut meat off bone.
Cut potatoes into chunks and put in the broth with meat chunks.
When potatoes are almost done, mix up noodles.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients except popcorn and soda in bowl.
Microwave on High 2 minutes and stir, 1 minute and stir, 1 minute and stir. Add soda, it will foam.
Pour over popcorn in brown paper grocery bag and shake.
Place folded bag in microwave for 1 minute and shake 2 times and for 30 seconds and shake 2 times.
Pour on baking sheet to dry.
When dry, store in airtight container.

title: amos chicken
directions: Boil or steam broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Boil chicken until done; remove bones and cut into pieces.
In a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish, layer the following ingredients:
cream of chicken soup, broccoli (salt and pepper to taste), sprinkle half of the cheese, chicken, sprinkle rest of cheese, cream of mushroom soup and cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange and pineapple salad
directions: Mix drained pineapple and orange pieces. Add cottage cheese and mix well. Pour dry Jell-O powder over mixture and stir well. Add Cool Whip and stir. Pour into a large salad bowl and refrigerate. Sets quickly and keeps well.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix all ingredients, adding cornbread mix last.
Pour in baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole delight
directions: Mix all together; put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil; put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake the next day for 1 hour at 325°, or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raspberry-rice salad
directions: Add milk and sugar to rice.
Cook slowly for approximately 25 minutes, until milk is gone.
Cool.
Stir in whipped cream.
Drain raspberries, reserving juice.
Add cornstarch to juice; heat until smooth.
Add raspberries and cook an additional 3 minutes.
Cool and top over rice.

title: chicken with honey-raisin sauce for two
directions: In saute pan, heat olive oil and saute garlic and shallot; add ground pepper and salt.
Strain ingredients from oil and place chicken breasts in oil.
Split breasts before cooking.
Brown 3 minutes on each side at medium-high heat so breasts are sealed. Add 1/4 cup wine and cover for 5 minutes.
Remove chicken breasts from pan.
Add carrots.
Return garlic and shallot to pan.
Add butter to pan.
Cook until carrots begin to turn brown.
Add bell pepper.
Add cayenne pepper; remove vegetables.
Add rest of wine, Worcestershire sauce, sugar*, raisins, oregano and parsley. Deglaze pan and reduce heat to a simmer and let sauce reduce. Rice the potatoes.
Pour thin layer sauce in plate.
Place chicken breasts in center; layer carrots over chicken and sprinkle riced potatoes on top and pour sauce over that.
Add a slice of fresh bread and garnish with broccoli.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and heat in microwave.
Add to warm cooked rice along with cheese and margarine.
Stir well until cheese and margarine are melted.
Place in casserole dish and bake until set well.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add Karo and mix well.
Add flavoring and pecans.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: surprise cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes with fork and pour pineapple juice over cake while hot.
Mix pudding with milk and vanilla. Stir until it starts to thicken.
Pour over cake.
After pudding sets, cover cake with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: bitoks au vin rouge
directions: Crumble slices of stale bread and soak in milk.
Add ground beef (chuck) and onion (finely chopped) and sauteed in butter; add beaten eggs, uncooked white cornmeal, salt, pepper and a little nutmeg.
Combine the mixture thoroughly and let it stand for 1 hour or more.

title: sauteed apples
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet over low heat.
Add apples, stirring until coated with margarine.
Cover and saute, shaking skillet occasionally to prevent sticking, 5 to 10 minutes or until apples are tender.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 4.

title: fisherman's macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside.
Drain fish liquid and add to it enough milk to make 2 cups of liquid.
Flake fish.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to a rolling boil in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop from spoon onto ungreased baking sheet into mounds 3-inches apart.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed, golden brown and dry.
Allow to cool slowly.
Fill with filling.
Makes 10 to 12 large puffs.

title: orange walnut date bar(to be topped with walnut date bar frosting)
directions: Mix together
in
large bowl, margarine and brown sugar until light and
fluffy.	Beat
in egg, orange rind and orange juice. Add flour
and
mix
until	smooth.
Stir in dates and walnuts. Bake for
to
30 minutes at 350°.
Make frosting and add to top of bars when cool.

title: lee's fried rice
directions: Follow directions on box in preparing fried rice. Fry the potato, add onion, green pepper, mushrooms, bean sprouts, fried rice, eggs, spice salt, pepper, soy sauce. Cook on low heat about 20 minutes.

title: tangy sweet meatballs(i serve these often on holidays.)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in margarine.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine preserves and barbecue sauce; mix well.
Pour evenly over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve in chafing dish.
Yield: 7 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Make a hole in the dry ingredients and add the oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix together well.
Then mix in pecans.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Fill each with 1/2 of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can substitute walnuts for pecans.

title: california vegetable pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Saute zucchini and green pepper in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add dill weed.
Make crust from the dough.
Place meat and half of the cheese, then the vegetables in pie shell.
Add remainder of cheese and top with tomato slices.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with sour cream or plain yogurt topping.

title: gloria's sweet potato casserole(my husband loves this casserole; it's a great dessert.)
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat until smooth.
Combine 1/4 cup evaporated milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well.
Press 1/2 cake mixture into 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan. Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: onion-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup cracker crumbs in a greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
In large skillet melt 1/4 cup butter over medium heat.
Add onions.
Cook until tender.
Spoon onions over cracker crumbs.
In same skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Stir constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Pour cheese mixture over onions.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with red pepper and jalapenos.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over soda and mix in the remaining ingredients and enough flour to handle.
May be dropped or rolled out.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken yum
directions: Mix together the cream of chicken soup and sherry.
Saute margarine and add dressing.
Place soup mixture over chicken and cheese.
Put dressing over all and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.
Serve with rice. Makes 8 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Split muffin and toast lightly.
Spread a little butter or margarine on top along with a tablespoon of spaghetti sauce.
Lay one or two slices of cheese on top of sauce.
Place muffin pizza under the broiler and heat until cheese is melted.

title: feather-light muffins
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Roll warm muffins in melted butter, then in sugar mixture. Serve warm. Yields 8 to 10 muffins.

title: olive-nut sandwich filling
directions: Use no salt!
Mash softened cream cheese with a fork, then add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped pecans, salad olives, olive juice and a dash of pepper.
Do not add salt! Mix well.

title: dixie pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot fat; sprinkle with salt and salt.
Place in baking dish; top with apple ring.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix whipped topping and condensed milk.
Add frozen lemonade (do not dilute or unthaw).
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 pie shells (either baked and cooled pastry or graham cracker, your choice).
Let it stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Serve cold.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together.
Drain pineapple good to mix into milk and lemon juice.
Add pecans and Cool Whip and mix.
Divide into the 2 crusts.
Put plastic cover on pie and freeze until ready to use.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream all ingredients, except for cake mix.
Add cake mix last and mix well.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook and drain well the broccoli.
Beat egg.
Add butter and soup; mix well.
Stir in broccoli, cheese and onion.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs; dot with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat well.
Then add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: sweet potato pie house of jackson
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter, salt, milk and spices.
Blend egg mixture with mashed sweet potatoes and lemon or orange juice. Pour into unbaked pie shell or 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Garnish with pecan halves, if desired.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375°; bake 40 minutes longer, or until golden brown.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients thoroughly (dough will be stiff). Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set but not hard, 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool about 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients, then add next 3 ingredients.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Pile on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir often.
Yields 6 to 8 quarts.
Put in decorator canister for a great gift idea.

title: mock guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Makes about 1 cup dip.
Serving per tablespoon contains 7 calories and 0 gm fat.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Layer all ingredients in a casserole dish as follows: seasoning to taste as you go, beef, beans, potatoes, onion and soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: sausage and kluski noodles
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, garlic and onion.
Add cream, cheese, parsley and marjoram.
Blend together and mix into cooked kluski noodles.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 4 hours covered at 300°. Do not remove cover for 4 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown and drain hamburg and sausage.
Add spices and mushrooms.
Add sauce to mak a thick scurry (too thin will make pie runny).
Simmer while preparing pie, stirring regularly. Grease large pan with butter.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix eggs in a small bowl.
Pour (well rinsed with cold water) spaghetti in large bowl.
Melt stick of butter and pour over spaghetti, stir in eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix good (may have to use hands). Form a thick crust in pan heavier around the edges, fairly thick on bottom.
Spread Ricotta cheese over entire bottom.
Fill pan about halfway up with sauce, then sprinkle half of Mozzarella cheese, put balance of sauce, then sprinkle balance of Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is brown.
Let cool for about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together, store and use as needed.
When ready to serve, when given in a special container.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat eggs with water, add mixes slowly; add melted butter and chocolate chips.
Cook in greased, floured tube pan at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Morning preparations:
Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Let mixture cool completely.

title: green onion and cheddar biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 475°. Into a bowl, sift together the self-rising flour, cake flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt. Using your fingers or a pastry cutter, work the butter into the flour until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add the buttermilk, cheese, and green onions and using your hands or a rubber spatula, stir just until the buttermilk and flour come together to form a dough, being careful not to overmix.

title: kim's a-1 chicken
directions: In small pot, mix and heat first six ingredients.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Fifteen minutes before you serve, heat tortillas in a 325° oven until crisp.
In a soup pot, saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Stir in chili powder and oregano.
Stir in tomatoes, broth and water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for a few minutes. Add green pepper and corn.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apricot cheese delights
directions: Drain and chill 1 large can apricots, chopped.
Add 1 large can crushed pineapple (reserve juice).
Dissolve apricot Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add reserved juice and chill until slightly congealed.
Add miniature marshmallows and drained fruit.
Pour and chill in 9 x 13-inch baking dish until set.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the fruit cocktail and the pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix over the cherries.
Dot with the margarine.
Add the pecans, if desired.
Bake in oven at 325°.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Beat the above ingredients for 4 minutes.
Then add oranges and beat until pieces are small.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25-30 minutes at 350°.

title: feta-tomato crostini
directions: Brush cut side of each roll with olive oil; place on baking sheet. Broil 6-inches from heat (with electric oven door partially opened) 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Place cheese evenly on each roll. Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder. Place tomatoes over cheese; drizzle with balsamic vinegar and sprinkle with mint. Serve on lettuce leaves and garnish, if desired. Serve immediately. Yield: 6 servings.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread; place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Brown sausage; drain.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper; pour this mixture in baking dish over other ingredients.

title: brunch strada
directions: Place bread and ham cubes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine milk, eggs, cheese and seasonings in blender.
Blend until cheese is grated.
Stir in chilies.
Pour over bread and ham, making sure all cubes are moistened.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angie's delicious cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix or blend all of the ingredients except pie filling until very smooth and then pour into your graham cracker crust pie shell. Let stand in refrigerator for at least about 30 minutes, then add the cherry pie filling on top and let it stand at least another 30 minutes.
Pie should be now ready to serve.

title: crusty cornbread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Place bacon drippings in a 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Heat at 425° for 5 minutes.
Remove skillet from oven and pour hot drippings into batter; mix well. Quickly pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt butter, add onions and celery and saute.
Add mushrooms, water, beef consomme and wild rice.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili crock-pot
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Add meat to crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours. Add fresh chopped peppers and red onions.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut up. Place in large bowl.

title: granger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and flavoring. Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt mixture.
Fold in dry cereal and coconut, chips or raisins.
Roll in small balls and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Bring crescent rolls and cream cheese to room temperature. Spread 1 package of rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: In 9-inch pan, combine nuts, brown sugar and butter.
Spread evenly on bottom of pan.
Place bottom pie crust over pecan mixture in pan.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon into crust lined pan.
Top with second crust and flute.
Cut slits in several places.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until crust is browned and apples are tender.
Cool pie 5 minutes.
Place serving plate over pie and invert.
Carefully remove pie pan.
Some nuts may remain in pan; place them on pie with knife or spatula. Cool at least 1 hour before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw and drain frozen broccoli in microwave.
Mix in eggs, sour cream and cornbread mix.
Pour mixture in ungreased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake approximately 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cheese wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Place a drinking glass in center of serving platter.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of mixture to form ring around glass.
Shape with a spatula to form "wreath".
Remove glass.
Garnish top with chopped parsley to look like wreath greeneries.
Serve with crackers.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl; add apples to mix.
Add lemon juice and mix thoroughly.
Place pie dough in a 9-inch pan. Add apple mixture.
Drizzle molasses over top of apples.
Cut butter into small pieces and place over top.
Add top crust, making a few slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, then cover edge of crust with foil to keep it from burning and continue baking for another 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: baked french doughnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add dry ingredients (mixed together) alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake 25 minutes.
When done, brush with melted butter and roll in mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain.
Add seasoning and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and onion rings.
Bake with grated cheese on top at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl.
Makes 1 punch bowl full.
If too strong, add more ginger ale (no water).

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then add milk.
Work together with flour until stiff enough to roll out.
Roll out real thin and let set for 2 hours or more.
Cut into narrow strips.
Cook in broth until done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and cooking oil.
Add and beat well the eggs, red food coloring and vinegar.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Add alternately to sugar mixture the dry ingredients, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball with beef
directions: Let cheese soften.
Combine all ingredients with cheese and form into a ball.
Roll in parsley or pecans.

title: deadman's casserole
directions: Brown onions in grease; add meat and cook until brown.
Add soups; stir well.
Add water and mushrooms.
Cook noodles and mix with meat.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: smoked sausage au gratin
directions: Cook sausage and onion in skillet until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Add potatoes, sausage mix, 2 1/2 cups water and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, mixing gently.
Simmer for 10 minutes longer or until carrots are tender-crisp.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook for 5 to 10 minutes longer or until broccoli is tender.

title: luncheon chicken squares
directions: Unroll dough and fit into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cover dough with the cheese, then add peas. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over peas. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Do not brown;
let set for 10 minutes before cutting squares. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion, parsley, garlic powder and oregano; simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Shred cheese and in 3-quart baking dish (oblong if available), layer 1/2 sauce, noodles and cheese; repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serves about 4.

title: plain pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Make depression in center and add milk, then egg.
Stir.
Add water to thin.
Any leftover can be kept in Tupperware for several days.

title: herbed melba toast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread.
Roll each slice of bread (with a rolling pin) as thin as possible.
Trim crusts.
Brush both sides of bread with butter mixture.
Slice bread diagonally to make 2 triangles.
Bake about 7 minutes then turn and repeat.
Bake at 350°.
Each side should be lightly browned and crisp.
Cool on rack.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to directions on package; drain and cool.
Combine with remaining vegetables.
Mix flour, sugar and salt in a heavy pan.
Add vinegar and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Combine vegetables and dressing.
Chill thoroughly.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together tomatoes and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning to taste. Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread.
May be cooked on stove as a stew.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash lettuce and tear into bite-size pieces.
Chill as long as possible.
Prepare dressing.
Pour prepared Lawry's dressing, garlic, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and lemon juice into container; mix or shake well.
When ready to serve, place romaine in large bowl; pour dressing over and toss well.
Add cheese and toss.
Add croutons and toss.
Serve at once.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add large can of syrup, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Use greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour and mix well.
Pat out with hands and cut with glass or cookie cutter. Best to use wax paper.
Bake at 375° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Chop peppers and onion very fine.
Chop dried beef and mix everything together.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
May add raisins, nuts or chocolate chips as desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Melt ingredients together until liquified.
Marinate chicken overnight.
Place chicken in buttered casserole, skin side down.
Baste with the marinade often.
Turn and continue to baste until chicken is cooked and richly glazed. Cook at 375°.

title: pumpkin biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and nuts. Mix other ingredients and add to dry. Knead few strokes. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: brownies
directions: Grease pan. Beat eggs; add sugar. Melt chocolate, butter and vanilla. Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture. Fold in flour and salt. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple syrup
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add all liquid ingredients (except butter).
Bring to a boil for 1 full minute, stirring constantly. Melt butter.
Serve warm.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: In saucepan, combine gelatine, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in sweetened milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, cook, stirring constantly, until gelatine dissolves and mixture thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in pumpkin.
Mix well.
Pour into graham crust.
Chill 3 hours, or until set.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients;
spread
on
hamburger
buns.	Wrap in foil and bake in 250° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in chipped beef, onions, green pepper, black pepper and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour into a small baking dish and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot with chips or crackers.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding over it and stir.
Add drained oranges and grapes.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add bananas.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Mix butter, mustard, poppy seeds and onion. Spread on rolls. Put a slice of ham and cheese in each roll. Wrap in aluminum foil. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Makes four sandwiches.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients well; let stand for at least 2 hours.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Drop or roll in marble size balls onto cookie sheet.
Cook for 20 minutes or until lightly browned at 300° and roll in powdered sugar.

title: jamacian barbecue sauce
directions: Remember, this does not require cooking, just blend and refrigerate.
Heat prior to using.
Good for pork chops, meat loaf, hamburger patties, brisket and stew.

title: red cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Split layers after cooled.
Fill with icing.

title: date cookies
directions: Pinch and bake at 350° until done.

title: green beans and bean sprouts
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove, crumble and set aside.
Add soy sauce, vinegar and sugar to the green beans.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until the beans are tender. Add water chestnuts and bean sprouts and continue to cook 2 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken breast and dried beef casserole
directions: Pound chicken breasts to flatten them. In a 2-quart casserole dish, line bottom with dried beef. Place chicken breasts on top of dried beef. Place layer of dried beef on top of chicken breasts. Mix together sour cream and cream of chicken soup. Spread over all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Worcestershire sauce together.
Spread on single slice of bread.
Broil until meat and cheese is heated and cheese melts.

title: daiquiri slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze. Serve with either sweet or sour mix.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, bring to boil.
Add peppers and garlic.
Cook until thick.
Put in jars.
Yields 10 or 12 pints.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, chicken and evaporated milk.
Boil margarine and chicken broth.
Take off stove and add stuffing.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cilantro-tomato salad
directions: Cube tomatoes.
Dice onion; combine.
Add celery, cilantro and seasonings.
This is great with meats or as a simple summer salad.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil the oleo, cocoa and water; pour over the flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: one chess pie
directions: Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Then add milk and eggs. Add melted margarine and beat.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake slowly.

title: rose's old-fashioned beef stew
directions: In large pot, brown beef cubes in lite Italian salad dressing, onion soup mix and garlic cloves.
Add lemon pepper, liquid dill spice, Italian seasoning, white vinegar, water, seasoned salt, paprika, parsley flakes and grape jelly.
Simmer, covered, on low heat for 60 minutes.
Add 1 cup water and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours longer, until meat is tender.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients to make a syrup and pour over the combined vegetables.
Store in a gallon glass jar and refrigerate. Ready to eat in 24 hours.
Will keep 1 year in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix Crisco and sugar; blend well.
Slowly add eggs 1 at a time, blend slowly. Add flour.
Mix buttermilk with baking soda, then add to mixture. Add vanilla; blend.
Bake 1hour and 35 minutes.
Cool, slice and eat.

title: viola's marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Mix all vegetables together and pour cool liquid over all and chill.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix and pour over salad.

title: pop's chuck roast
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over roast. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grate all ingredients and
work all the juice out.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and
salt to taste.
Mix together and make sandwiches.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a bowl until fluffy.
Add the egg; combine well.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Stir into butter mixture, blending well.
Add chocolate chips, almonds and orange peel.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, at least 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake cookies at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown and crisp.
Let cookies cool for a minute on sheet, then remove to wire rack.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pork roast
directions: In a shallow baking dish in a 350° oven roast a 2 to 4 pound boneless pork rib end roast for 20 minutes.
Baste with mixture. Continue to roast, basing occasionally, 20 to 30 minutes more, until thermometer inserted reaches 155° to 160° or until done.

title: easy oven rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a
10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more. Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serves 6.

title: never weep meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water together until clear, like starch.
Stir and cook.
This takes only a few minutes.
Cool while heating egg whites.
Beat egg whites until standing in peaks.
Then add first mixture and beat some more, adding 6 tablespoons more sugar, one at a time while beating.
Beat until all stands in high peaks.
Put on pie and brown in a 350° oven.

title: orange buttermilk muffins
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add egg; mix well and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix together the flour, soda and salt.
Chop the orange half in a blender with the buttermilk or yogurt.
Add alternately the flour mixture to the sugar mixture, stirring only until the ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 9 to 12 small muffins.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients into cake pan.
Make three small holes in this mixture and put vinegar, vanilla and shortening in holes. Pour water over and mix until smooth.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Double for sheet cake.

title: johnnycake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add milk, eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes. Makes 1 8 x 10 loaf.

title: millie's congo bars
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine butter and brown sugar and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add them to the batter with the mixer set on its lowest speed, mixing until dry ingredients are blended thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate bits and walnuts.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until set and lightly browned.
Cool completely and cut into 24 bars.
Store in airtight container.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Stew with 1 teaspoon salt until tender.
In a double boiler, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add onion and bacon chips, if desired.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Stir until thick, adding more milk until desired consistency (you may use water from potatoes).
Add potatoes and cheese.
Mix well.
Delicious served with corn bread.

title: festive fudge
directions: Mix in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over top).
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in until completely melted 6 ounce package (1 cup) semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Stir in 1 cup cut up nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into 30 pieces.

title: fruit cupcakes
directions: Cream together.
Place paper cups in cupcake tins; fill 2/3rd full.
Cook 40 minutes in 300° oven; edges should be brown.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Melt one stick of butter and 1 package of Ritz crackers.
Combine and use as topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass jar.
Cover; shake well.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rinse lettuce and dry. Tear into large pieces. Wrap in paper towels and refrigerate for several hours to crisp the lettuce. Combine everything but the lettuce and the croutons in a blender and puree until smooth. When ready to serve, place the dressing into the bottom of a very large pan or bowl and toss thoroughly with the lettuce; transfer to a salad bowl, sprinkle with croutons and serve immediately with freshly ground pepper.

title: potato-tuna casserole
directions: Bake potatoes and scoop out center.
Keep the shells.
Combine mashed potatoes, tuna, onions, olives, cheese, green pepper, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Spoon back in potato shells.
Bake at 350° on a cookie sheet until onion and peppers are done.
Serve with a spoon of sour cream and chives on top.
Add salad and hot rolls for a complete meal.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage in skillet and drain.
Put the 6 slices of bread, buttered generously, buttered side down, in an oblong casserole dish.
Put sausage on top of bread.
Then layer shredded sharp cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour this on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
This can be made the evening before.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread in bowl.
Add Pepperidge Farm seasoning mix. Add onion and celery.
Beat eggs and add.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in chicken broth until slightly soupy.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cooked chicken may be placed on top of dressing before baking.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine egg with milk and blend thoroughly.
Add to dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
The dough should be the consistency of a soft drop biscuit dough.
Drop by spoonfuls on boiling stew and cook about 12-15 minutes.
Do not raise lid while dumplings are steaming.

title: ramen noodle cole slaw
directions: Mix cole slaw mix with crumbled dry Ramen noodles, sunflower seeds, onions and almonds in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until time of serving.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
In food processor, puree beans (or mash by hand), lemon juice, cumin, garlic and pepper.
Transfer to bowl, cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Sprinkle with green onions just before serving.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: italian chicken & sausage with peppers
directions: Heat oil in pressure cooker. Prick skin of sausages in several places with a fork. Add the sausages and chicken to the oil and cook until well browned on all sides.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips. Blend well. Add chips. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a tube or Bundt pan.

title: my mom's raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 5 minutes.
When cool, add baking soda.
Cream sugar and margarine and add eggs.
Add flour with the rest of the dry ingredients, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: barbara's jewish apple cake
directions: It is never too soon to do something nice for someone - because you never know how soon it will be too late.

title: twice baked potato
directions: In 400° oven, bake potatoes about 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in 1/2 lengthwise.
Scoop potato out and place in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spoon filling back into potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes and then serve.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from meat; brown on all sides in oil in heavy pan.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients to meat.
Cover pan tightly and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is very tender. Stir and turn meat every 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sweetened condensed milk, cocoa, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Using medium heat, slowly stir in water.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
(Best if mixed with electric mixer.)
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: hot creamy fudge sauce
directions: Combine milk, margarine and salt in a saucepan.
Heat on low until margarine melts.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
(May require use of a whisk.)
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter or margarine, sugar and salt. Add eggs and beat after each, alternating with flour, milk and flavoring of your choice.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 1/4 hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Start oven at moderate (350°).
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease paper.
Cream shortening and sugar together in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add applesauce and mix.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat into batter until smoothly combined.
Add currants.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Let cool in pan.
Makes 8 or more servings.
A good brunch cake.

title: hazelnut cake
directions: Have all the ingredients at room temperature, especially the butter and the eggs.
In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and 1 cup of the sugar until very light and fluffy, 3 to 5 minutes in a mixer.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Beat in the vanilla, then the hazelnuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and stir over medium heat until blended.

title: frozen pudding on a stick
directions: Combine condensed milk and water; mix well.
Add pudding; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Pour equal amounts into cups.
Insert wooden sticks into center of each cup.
Freeze 6 hours.
To serve, remove from freezer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Peel off paper cup.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in 8 x 10-inch buttered baking dish.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add juices.
