Fill freezer containers, leaving space for freezing.
Let thaw slightly before serving.
Makes 80 cups.

title: special brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Mix, adding one at a time, the rest of the ingredients, well.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: marino's velveeta melt
directions: Melt cheese and salsa in a 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High for about 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Serve hot with crackers, chips or cut up vegetables.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Season chicken.
Let stand overnight.
Broil chicken until tender.
Spread with barbecue sauce.
Cover with foil and bake until sauce is in chicken.
Serve hot!

title: macaroni pastitsio (a greek dish)
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large skillet, saute onions in butter until golden.
Add beef and brown evenly.
Stir in tomato puree, tomato paste, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Add bread crumbs.
Beat egg in a large kettle, add macaroni and toss.

In a large rectangular baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches), arrange in layers half of macaroni, the meat mixture, remaining macaroni and then rich white sauce on top, sprinkling each layer with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven 30 minutes, or until cheese browns lightly.
Let stand 10 minutes, then cut into square portions.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mama's prune cake(80 years in family)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir flour, soda, salt and spices. Add eggs to butter and sugar; mix.
Combine with flour mix; stir in buttermilk.
Grease Bundt pan and coat with flour.
Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean.

title: veal romano
directions: Pound each veal slice to tenderize.
Coat with flour.
Layer 1 slice each of Prosciutto and cheese on each piece of veal.
Roll up; score with toothpick.
Heat margarine in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat until melted.
Cook veal rolls in margarine, turning occasionally until brown.
Add wine; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium-high heat for 4 minutes. Serves 4.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in egg yolks.
Heat milk in saucepan.
Add some of the hot milk to egg yolks and stir. Add this to the rest of the milk in saucepan with the coconut and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Turn into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: easy pickles
directions: Fill jars with pickles, then add cold water.
The first four ingredients should be added to each quart jar.
Seal.
Before using, about 12 to 24 hours ahead of time, remove from brine. Wash in cold water twice and drain.
Split each pickle and return to rinsed jar.
Add sugar and cold water.
Place in refrigerator and keep refrigerated.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix.
Heat to blend (in microwave).
Serve with French bread. Cut in pieces.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Chill thoroughly.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook slowly in a large pot to	soft ball (230°).
Add peanuts and salt; cook to hard crack (310°), stirring constantly.
Add butter and soda.	Stir to
blend (will
bubble up).
Add vanilla; pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Pull out with a spoon or spatula.	Cool.
Break apart.
Store in an airtight container.

title: stuffed portobello mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, basil, garlic and rosemary. Saute until onion is soft (less than 5 minutes).
Transfer to medium bowl; mix in shrimp, bread crumbs, cheese and mayo. Lightly season with salt and pepper.
Remove dark gills from mushrooms.
Arrange mushrooms rounded side down onto an oiled baking sheet.
Mount the shrimp filling into mushrooms, pressing to compact.
Can make ahead to keep in refrigerator for later. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Spicy version: Lightly sprinkle with red pepper before baking.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Prepare at night and put in salt water overnight.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend chili sauce and mayonnaise together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Great with chips and crackers. (I usually double this.)

title: russian tea
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to hot water about 1 tablespoon per cup.
Store in an airtight container.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread mixture into pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Cut into squares. Eat warm or cold.
Cook about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave divinity
directions: In 3-quart bowl, cook sugar, syrup and water 12 minutes and 30 seconds on High power (should be fine thread).
Add salt to egg whites and beat them on high speed until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup in a thin stream into the egg whites, beating constantly, until mixture loses its shine and thickens.
Stir in vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoon at once on waxed paper or foil.
Makes about 30 pieces.
Use a heavy mixer to beat.
Hand mixers do not have enough power.

title: easy cherry pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add milk, blend thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust. Chill 2 hours or until set. Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sweet peas and potato dish
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 3-quart pan until soft.
Add potatoes and cook until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: macaroni franks casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed. Drain well. In glass casserole dish, combine all the ingredients.
Cook, covered, 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish.
Rest 5 minutes, then serve.

title: chicken taco salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil over medium-high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in salsa; cover 5 minutes.
Stir together salad dressing, avocado and hot pepper sauce.
To serve, layer chips, lettuce, beans, chicken, tomatoes and avocado mixture on serving plate.
Top with cheese. Makes 4 servings.
Prep time:
20 minutes.

title: macaroni & cheese bake
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water. Drain. Mix together all ingredients. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle paprika over top. Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until sides of dish show macaroni is browning. Serve hot.

title: hot dish
directions: Line an electric frypan with strips of bacon.
Crumble ground beef on top of that.
Add, in layers, sliced onion, potatoes, carrots and cabbage.
Turn up heat to slightly fry the meat to low and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Mix all other ingredients together in order.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: brasciole
directions: Note:
Amount of meat depends on number of people for dinner. Usually, a flank steak for Brasciole for one person is 5 x 8-inches.
If you prefer one to two large Brasciole to add to sauce-gravy, the size can be larger and, once it is cooked, you can slice it.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, spread pineapple on bottom. (Optional: 1/3 cup sugar can be added on top of pineapple.) Then spread cherry pie filling on top of pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of cherry pie filling. Slice butter and put on top of dry cake mix. Top with nuts. Bake in oven at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat buttermilk pancakes
directions: In blender or mixer blend together egg whites, buttermilk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop 1/2 cup of batter on hot, oiled skillet.
Brown on both sides.
For thinner or thicker pancakes, use more or less buttermilk.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with bacon and olives.
Bake for 1 hour in a 325° oven.
This dish can be made ahead.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix ingredients, except brown sugar and boiling water; set aside.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place the brown sugar and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Pour batter mixture onto first mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Good served with whipped topping.

title: gooey buns
directions: Grind, chop or process all of ingredients.
Spread on hamburger buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil individually.
Refrigerate. When someone needs a sandwich, pop one in a 325° oven until hot, about 20 minutes.
Or wrap in microwave wax paper and heat.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch, salt and water. Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly. Beat together egg yolks and lemon juice. Add small amount of hot mixture to yolks first, then stir into custard and cook until mixture comes to a full boil again. Remove from heat. Stir in lemon rind and butter. Cover while making meringue.

title: cherry pretzel delight
directions: Combine pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pour on butter and mix.
Press into pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes and cool. Soften the cream cheese and whip.
Add the powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip (not with beater).
Spread on crust.
Cool.
Pour the cherry pie filling on top.

title: crabmeat dish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spread in dish.
Spread 1/2 jar chili sauce on top.
Spread 8 to 10 ounces crabmeat on top. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve on crackers.

title: mama's christmas pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into pudding dish. Cover with crumbled wafers.
Bake in 350° oven until pudding is firm, when toothpick comes out clean.

title: pasta and peas
directions: Chop and fry onion in
a little oil.
Cover and simmer until soft.
Add peas and ham if you wish.
Cook all together.
Add a small can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water.
Salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Cook until soft.

title: mix and match vegetable snack
directions: Spread celery stalks with peanut butter or cream cheese.
Eat it all up!

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Prepare Stove top stuffing mix according to package directions.
Saute mushrooms in pan sprayed with Pam, until slightly browned.
Spread out in casserole dish.
Spread out stuffing mix on top.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and pour reserved liquid and milk over all.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; crush crackers and mix with butter. Cover top with crackers mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer with lettuce, macaroni, diced eggs, peas, ham (shredded) and cheese.
Onions may be added here or used in dressing.
Mix together salad dressing, sour cream, mustard and hot sauce.
Put this all over the top, sealing edges with dressing.
Refrigerate overnight and toss before serving.

title: opera squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour thoroughly with a pastry blender. Pat lightly into a greased 7 x 11-inch oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cover with the balance of the ingredients mixed as follows:
Beat eggs until light; add brown sugar and flour and mix until smooth.
Add walnuts, coconut and vanilla and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Let cool a little and cut into squares.

title: taffy apple pie
directions: Put apples in crust. Pour Eagle Brand on. Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: dainty little tea cookies
directions: In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat flour, margarine, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber scraper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
On lightly floured surface with floured hands, shape dough into small balls each using about 1 teaspoon of dough.
Place cookies on ungreased large cookie sheet; with side of fork or edge of knife, mark each cookie crosswise several times.
Bake cookies 10 to 15 minutes until lightly golden.
Cool 5 minutes, then gently remove with spatula.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: avocado ice cream
directions: Peel avocado and blend in blender with other ingredients until smooth.
Put into electric ice cream maker and freeze as directions per freezer directions.

title: coconut pie baked in crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie crust for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Mix whole wheat flour, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Add water, honey and shortening; heat on low for 1 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat on medium for 1 minute, scraping bowl again.
Stir in remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, until easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface; knead 10 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl; cover to let rise in warm place.
When doubled in size, punch down and divide into 2 loaf pans.
Allow to rise again.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: first rate chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Mix egg yolks and milk together; add to dry ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: easy ice cream dessert
directions: Let ice cream come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients and refreeze.

title: potato-pork chop bake
directions: Peel and slice enough potatoes to cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour enough milk to cover potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with pork chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn chops after 30 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Arrange Tater Tots in casserole dish. Heat together the browned meat, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over Tater Tots; mix together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly in the middle.
Great for kids!

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mix margarine and cracker crumbs together and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, then mix in crumb mixture, leaving enough to spread on top.
Bake 35 minutes or more if needed at 350° until nicely browned.

title: fruity french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in screw-top jar or small bowl.
Shake well or whip with wire whisk until ingredients are well blended and of a thick and creamy consistency.
Chill.
Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
Shake well before using.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten rolls on cookie sheet.
Pinch perforations together. Bake as directed.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed and garlic powder well.
Spread over crust after it has cooled, about 10 minutes.
Top with vegies and garnish with Cheddar cheese.

title: gourmet potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, salt, water and bouillon cubes in a large saucepan.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add 1 cup milk to hot mixture.
In large bowl or measuring pitcher, blend sour cream with chives, flour and remaining milk.
Pour sour cream mixture into potato mixture and stir over low heat until thickened.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cracker crumbs in a buttered dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: minestrone casserole
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Cook sausage and celery in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sausage is done.
Drain.
Mix sausage mixture, spaghetti, sauce mix and remaining ingredients in ungreased 3-quart casserole or rectangular baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Break up tomatoes.
Cover and bake about 50 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir.
Let stand uncovered about 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: island sweet-sour meatballs
directions: In bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, milk and the 3/4 teaspoon salt. Add meat; mix well. Shape mixture into 24 (1-inch) meatballs (1 tablespoonful each). In a large skillet, brown the meatballs in hot shortening. Drain off fat. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; cut pineapple into small wedges and set aside. Add water to reserved syrup to make 3/4 cup. Combine syrup mixture, cranberry sauce, barbecue sauce, the 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Pour over meatballs in skillet. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Slowly blend the 1/4 cup cold water into the cornstarch.
Stir into skillet. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add pineapple and green pepper. Simmer, covered, until pepper is barely tender. Serve mixture over hot cooked rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: out of this world pie
directions: In a saucepan combine cherry pie filling with sugar, pineapple and juice, cornstarch and food coloring; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Allow to cool.
Add bananas and pecans. Pour into 2 baked pie shells and top with whipped topping.
Keep pie in refrigerator.
I add the whipped topping when ready to serve it.
It is also good with ice cream or no topping.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and combine with rest of the ingredients. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: If you use real tart apples, you can use Splenda for sweetness.

title: lyn's quiche
directions: Place mixture into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Combine and simmer, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: ham rolls
directions: Have butcher slice ham paper thin.
Combine cream cheese, nuts and garlic; add small amount of mayonnaise.
Do not get mixture too thin.
Spread each slice of ham with mixture; roll as for jelly roll.
Chill thoroughly; cut into slices.
Serve each slice on round cracker.

title: heavenly honey fruit dressing
directions: Crush strawberries; add honey and lemon juice.
Fold into sour cream.
Spoon over fruit.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: grandma's dumplings
directions: Beat butter (softened at room temperature) with eggs until well blended.
Add self-rising flour until thoroughly combined. Drop by tablespoon into just simmering broth.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed broiled avocados(a hot side dish.)
directions: Saute scallions in olive oil; reduce heat.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add 1/4 cup bread crumbs, mix and set aside.

title: blackberry wine
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a 1-quart wide mouth canning jar.
It will be a tight fit.
Make sure you firmly pack down each layer in place before adding the flour mixture.

title: bet-you-can't-eat-just-one chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, oil, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt, beating well.
Stir in chips.

title: grandpa's soup
directions: In a saucepan, brown meat. Add chili powder and tomato juice. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. While this is simmering, cook potatoes and onions until tender. Cook macaroni according to directions. Add macaroni and mixed vegetables to the meat mixture. Simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: mountain apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar; blend well. Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour hot topping over it in pan.
Let cool. When completely cool, remove from pan.
(Check cake at 50 minutes with toothpick.
If it comes out dry looking, leave it out and it will finish baking with its own heat.)

title: italian tortellini salad
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 6 cups water to a boil. Add the tortellini. Reduce the heat slightly. Cook in gently boiling water for about 10 minutes or until tender. Drain tortellini in a colander.
Place in a large bowl of ice cold water.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Drain well. Transfer chilled tortellini to
a serving bowl. Add cheese, tomatoes, pepper strips, olives and green onions.
Pour the dressing over the tortellini mixture and toss gently to coat. Add Parmesan cheese and toss lightly.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter, sugar and 2 tablespoons pineapple syrup in oven. Remove and arrange pineapple rings and cherries in pan.
Prepare batter as directed on cake package.
Pour over mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Let cool 5 minutes in pan.
Invert on serving plate and allow 2 to 3 minutes before removing pan.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin banana bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine pumpkin, bananas, sugar and oil; mix well.
Beat in one egg at a time.
In another bowl mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and salt; sift together.
Add to pumpkin mix and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch).
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool before cutting.
Can make ahead and freeze.

title: original margarita
directions: Pour over ice in shaker.
Shake vigorously.
Pour into preferred drinking glass.

title: purple lady
directions: Whip cream.
Then dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water. Stir in blueberry pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Chill about 1/2 hour until it begins to thicken.
Add bananas and whipped cream by folding.

title: lo-cal grilled chicken
directions: Mix dressings into bowl, then dip each portion into mixture. Place chicken on preheated grill; cook for approximately 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: brownies
directions: Melt cocoa and margarine; cool.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix all by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Set aside and cook until lukewarm.
Mix next 3 ingredients and let this yeast mixture set until yeast is dissolved.
Place 6 cups unsifted flour in large bowl.
Pour all ingredients over flour and stir with spoon.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well with spoon (not mixer).
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 5 to 8 days.
Roll out and shape rolls as desired.
Let rolls rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and stir in remaining ingredients.
Top with crushed cheese crackers and pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Mix together and pat into bottom of baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, crush Oreos.
Spread a layer of crushed Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan or a flowerpot, then a layer of mixture, more cookies and top with flowers and gummy worms for a nice touch.

title: peanut butter pie from papa nick's
directions: Cream peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until serving time.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and chopped nuts together in a large bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix with your hands until light and crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of the mixture to be used later as a topping.
Place reminder in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly. Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: granny p's banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add bananas and mix well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture along with oatmeal. Stir in nuts and flavoring.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: quick sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Put jelly and chili sauce in saucepan.
Whisk until smooth. Let simmer for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, make meatballs the size of a quarter.
Put meatballs in sauce.
Let simmer for 25 minutes and serve with toothpicks.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Boil water. Stir in sugar and jello.
Place in refrigerator and jell until livery.
Whip Carnation milk (which has been refrigerated 1 day). Fold into jello and stir in 2 tablespoons lemon juice (plus rind, if available).
Sprinkle half of graham cracker crumbs on bottom of a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Pour in lemon mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix dressing, preserves, soup mix and water in a bowl and stir until mixed.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add pineapple and pepper for the last 1/2 hour, uncovered.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add sour cream, egg and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Fold in apples and pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Put yellow cake mix in mixing bowl.
Add lemon jello to hot water; mix and let cool a little.
Add eggs, oil and jello to cake mix; beat well. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake test is done.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions until done.
Drain off fat and set meat aside.
Mix soup, sauce and water; heat and keep warm.
Dip tortillas in hot sauce and place a layer in 2-quart casserole. Add some meat, cheese and olives; then another layer of dipped tortillas, then meat, cheese and olives.
Repeat layers.
Pour remainder of sauce over all and sprinkle small amount of cheese and olives on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: hamburg and elbow casserole
directions: Boil water and then add the box of macaroni until done.
Chop onion and put in pan with hamburg until browned, then add the two cans of tomato soup.
Bring to a boil.
When macaroni is done, drain and add tomato soup and hamburg together.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: pancake chicken
directions: Prepare pancake batter according to directions for pancakes. Coat chicken pieces in batter. Then coat pieces in Shake-n-Bake.
Bake or deep fry until chicken is done. Serve with honey drizzled over it.

title: barbecue spoon burgers
directions: Brown ground chuck and remove excess fat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Mix well and add to starter. Mix slightly. Let stand on counter out of refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours. Feed first starter 2 times before making bread. This does not rise - only bubbles. Take out 1 cup starter (to make bread) and return remaining starter to refrigerator. Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days; feed again. If not making bread, throw out 1 cup starter, but it must be fed after 5 days.

title: meatballs(microwave)
directions: Mix together beef, egg, crumbs, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and chopped onions.
Shape into 12 balls and arrange in a circle in 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High 9 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes, until done.
Great in spaghetti sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: In
saucepan,
cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water for
minutes.
Drain.
Combine
soup, sour cream and carrots in a separate bowl.
Stir in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing
mix with margarine; spread half of stuffing mix
in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture
on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Leftovers can be frozen.)

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine and blend condensed milk, lemon juice, sugar and egg yolks.
Pour mixture over crushed vanilla wafer pie crust; top with meringue.

title: stuffed scallops(very old maine recipe)
directions: Combine melted butter, bread crumbs and sherry.
In buttered casserole alternate layers of scallops with crumb mixture and salt and pepper each layer of scallops lightly.
Pour evaporated milk over all and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: bachelors spuds
directions: Place potatoes into greased preheated skillet.
Slice onion, bell pepper, celery, carrot and bacon.
Saute.

title: vicki's broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, chopped eggs, celery, pickles, mayonnaise, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna i
directions: Lightly brown beef, onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water and spices.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan layer alternately sauce, noodles and the 3 cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with nonstick spray.
Layer chips almost to top of pan.
Mix chicken (take off of bone), enchilada sauce, soup and onion.
Pour over chips.
Spread cheese over top.
Then pour chicken broth over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract. Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn the mixture into pan.
Spoon the pie filling into the cake in 16 spots. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Heat on low, half and half.
Add margarine.
Add salt.
Place hash browns in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour creamed mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon bar
directions: Combine flour and butter; cut with fork like pie crust.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: world's greatest cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 45 minutes.
Use 13 x 19-inch pan.

title: turkey casserole
directions: In a
casserole
dish,	add
3	cups of turkey, 1/2 cup pimientos, 1/2
cup
chopped
olives
and
1/2 cup diced green chiles.
Pour
on
top 1 can of mushroom soup.
Add 1 1/2 cups of Cheddar cheese, 1 1/2 cups Jack cheese and 6 flour tortilla shells on	top.
Start over again in the same order for second layer. Add cheese and black olives on top of shells on second layer. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Soak beans.
Add ham hock and cook 1 hour.
Take out ham and dice.
Return to beans.
Add paste, onion, sugar and chiles. Simmer until done.

title: sugar-and-vinegar canned green beans
directions: Place beans in kettle.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar; add to beans and cover with water.
Boil 30 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain and set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, mustard and salt.
Heat until bubbly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve:
Place 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix in a cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: sausage cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Place slices of bread in bottom of a large 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown sausage and spread on top of bread.
Mix eggs, sour cream and milk.
Pour over sausage.
Top with cheese and onions.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: urb chicken
directions: Fry chicken breasts for 10 minutes and put in baking dish. Mix together soup, broth, celery and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: play dough for kids
directions: Mix in saucepan over low heat until thick.
Doesn't take long! Add food coloring of your choice.
(It can be added to the water or stirred in while mixing.)
After thick, take by handfuls and knead thoroughly.
This will store for a long time in sealed container.

title: bavarian cream salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple and juice.
Add sour cream, nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl the nuts, oranges slices, dates and coconut.
Pour the hot oleo over.
Mix in another bowl the sugar, buttermilk, soda, eggs and flour.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a tube or loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour or longer. Usually takes about 2 hours, but check after 1 hour cooking time.

title: string beans provencale
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, 8 minutes or until soft.
Add tomatoes, thyme, sugar, salt and pepper, breaking up tomatoes with back of spoon.
Stir in string beans; simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 25 to 35 minutes or until tender.
(Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.)
Serve hot or warm.

title: liz's cucumber pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Add cukes and onions. Boil 2 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: clam fritters
directions: Heat vegetable oil or shortening (3 to 4 inches) to 375° in deep fat fryer or heavy saucepan.
Beat flour, baking powder, salt, milk, egg and reserved clam liquid with hand beater until smooth.
Stir in clams.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: hamburg stew
directions: In a large kettle, scramble the hamburg and onion in a little oil.
Add carrots and cover with water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Lastly add diced potatoes and simmer for 1 hour more.
Thicken with flour and water or water and cornstarch.

title: apple dapple
directions: Mix eggs, white sugar and oil.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Add sifted ingredients to egg mixture.
Add apples, vanilla and nuts (if you want); mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Thaw bread dough as directed on package.
Roll out to conform to the size of a cookie sheet.
Place ham along center of 1/3 of the dough.
Top with sliced cheese.
Roll up jelly roll fashion. Moisten edge with water and seal.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Slice and serve warm.

title: crisp peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter.
Combine dry ingredients. Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes 6 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice, fruit cocktail, pineapple, mandarin oranges and pecans together well and pour into the graham cracker pie shells.
Chill for 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken in puff pastry
directions: Thaw puff pastry.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut in sections large enough to wrap a chicken breast.
Place chicken in center of pastry; with 1 tablespoon butter, 1 slice of cheese, salt and pepper.
Pinch pastry together and brush with milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla and rice.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart Pyrex dish; sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar mix.
Place Pyrex dish in a pan with hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Try inserting knife at 25 minutes; when it comes out clean, it's done.
Don't overbake.

title: autumn festival fluff
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well with fork and set aside. Combine the confectioners sugar and 1/3 cup peanut butter.
Mix until crumbly and set aside.
With a mixer, whip the cream cheese and sugar.
Fold cheese mixture into the whipped topping. Refrigerate.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the graham crumb mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of the cheese mixture over the crumbs.
Place apple slices (1 can of apple pie filling, 1 pound 4 ounce can).
Sprinkle with ground cinnamon.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the confectioners sugar mixture over the apples.
Top with remaining cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs, then confectioners sugar crumbs.
Cover with foil and chill for 24 hours before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: bonbon cookies
directions: Roll out vanilla wafers with a rolling pin until smooth and fine.
Sift the powdered sugar and cocoa.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and dip into melted chocolate chips and shortening mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold.

title: curried egg mold
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Sprinkle in curry powder; cook about 1 minute.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup chicken broth; add to remainder of broth (which you have heated in a microwave) to dissolve the gelatin.
Set aside about 1/4 cup to decorate the mold.
Stir into curry mixture and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cool.
As this is starting to thicken, add the remainder of the ingredients, plus a drop of yellow food coloring.
To decorate the top of the mold, pour in some of the reserved gelatin broth mixture.
When it is almost set, arrange sliced black olives on top.
When firm, add the remainder of the mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: yum yum cake or sock it to me cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, regular sugar, eggs, sour cream and flavoring.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in a tube pan, after mixing it all together, then pour in nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Now, pour in the other 1/2 of the cake mixture and cook at 375° until done.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and ice with the confectioners sugar and milk.

title: good popcorn balls
directions: Boil the ingredients in a thick saucepan to soft ball stage. I double this recipe for a large roaster of popped corn.
Cool a little.
Keep your hands greased with margarine and shape into balls.
Coloring can be added to boiled syrup if you want colored popcorn balls.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add mushrooms; cook 8 minutes or until juicy.
Add flour and cheese.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix together oil and cocoa.
Blend oil, sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Chill overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350°.
A topping can be use before baking.

title: one gallon refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir to dissolve.
Make alternate layers of onion and sliced cucumbers in gallon jar. When sugar is all dissolved, pour liquid over onion and cukes. Refrigerate for several days before using.
Keep in refrigerator. Will be good for several months.
These are very good.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Dissolve the sugar, vinegar and garlic salt together.
Pour over the salad.

title: "no fuss" or "honey-mustard" pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix approximately 4 tablespoons Gulden's mustard with brown sugar (enough to change color of mustard or to your taste).
Line baking pan with foil.
Coat both sides of pork chops with mustard/sugar mixture.
Place chops in baking pan and cover with foil (to keep moisture in).
Bake for 45 minutes (depending on thickness of pork chops, may need to adjust time).

title: sticky muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°, line muffin tins with papers.
Put 1 teaspoon honey in bottom of each muffin cup, top honey with 1 mandarin section.
Combine flour, oat bran, baking powder, salt and sugar, stir to mix.
Add mandarin peel, eggs, milk and melted butter and stir just until mixed.
Spoon batter over mandarin slices, fill each cup about 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until straw inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and onions in saucepan.
Boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain and mash.
Combine squash, cheese and ingredients; stir well and put in 2-quart casserole, lightly greased.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gratin of fresh spinach and mushrooms(a gourmet vegetable dish)
directions: Sweat shallots, garlic and mushrooms until tender.
Add spinach; cook until tender.
Add sherry, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and drain.
Place spinach-mushroom mixture in small casserole dish.
Top with reduced cream and cover with grated Parmesan cheese.
Gratin in a 400° oven until golden brown on top and cream is bubbling.
Serve right from the oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put water, Karo syrup and sugar in medium pan.
Do not stir. Cook until spins a thread on medium heat.
Do not rush or stir, then add peanuts and butter.
Cook until nuts are done.
Watch for color to change.
Very important.
When nuts are done golden brown, very quickly add the vanilla and soda.
Stir very fast. Pour into large pan and shake to smooth.
Pan needs to be buttered before pouring brittle into it.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put 1/2 of crumbled Oreos in dish; mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and pour over cookie crumbs.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla; add a layer on powdered sugar mixture.
Put Oreo cookie crumbs on top and press down.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in a greased baking dish (8-inch square pan).
Mix other 5 ingredients in a bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle this on top of apples and bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and brown sugar.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and pack down; cool.

title: hot breakfast grapefruit
directions: Seed, core and section grapefruit halves.
Place on serving dish.
Mix granola and honey.
Spread granola mixture over each half.
Microwave on High (100%) for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.

title: holiday butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add and combine flour, baking powder and salt to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Roll on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut desired shapes.
Place on ungreased sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
